0States%20of%20America.%20The%20party%20was%20founded%20in%201954%20by%20anti-slavery%20activists%20and%20opposed%20the%20expansion%20of%20chattel%20slavery%20in%20the%20USA.%20The%20party%E2%80%99s%20ideological%20plinth%20was%20classical%20liberalism.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EAs%20early%20as%20the%201870s%2C%20politicians%20and%20newspapers%20began%20to%20refer%20to%20the%20Republican%20Party%20as%20the%20grand%20old%20party%20to%20emphasise%20its%20role%20in%20preserving%20the%20Union%20during%20the%20Civil%20War.%20The%20party%20stood%20for%20the%20virtue%20of%20liberty%20and%20the%20basic%20creed%20of%20the%20US.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ELikewise%2C%20the%20Indian%20National%20Congress%20and%20the%20Sri%20Lankan%20United%20National%20Party%20(UNP)%20stood%20for%20liberty%2C%20equality%2C%20and%20fraternity%20in%20their%20respective%20countries.%20They%20have%20been%20epitomes%20of%20the%20composite%20culture%20and%20inclusive%20pluralism%20in%20their%20respective%20countries.%20In%20the%20past%20and%20present%2C%20these%20two%20grand%20old%20parties%20have%20been%20living%20a%20parallel%20life.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EThe%20splendid%20past%20and%20precarious%20future%C2%A0%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHistorian%20Ramachandra%20Guha%20in%20his%20essay%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20long%20life%20and%20lingering%20death%20of%20the%20Indian%20National%20Congress%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%20%3Cspan%3Eunderscores%20the%20unique%20significance%20of%20the%20Congress%20party%20in%20India%3A%20%E2%80%9CThe%20BJP%20is%20a%20party%20of%20Hindu%20majoritarians%20many%20of%20whose%20members%20tend%20to%20suspect%20and%20even%20demonise%20Muslims%20and%20Christians.%20For%20their%20part%2C%20the%20regional%20parties%20use%20the%20rhetoric%20of%20caste%20and%20linguistic%20discrimination%20mostly%20to%20advance%20the%20wealth%20and%20power%20of%20their%20leaders.%20The%20case%20of%20the%20Congress%20is%20different.%20This%20was%20the%20party%20that%20led%20the%20movement%20for%20freedom%2C%20the%20party%20that%20united%20India%20and%20brought%20people%20of%20different%20religions%20and%20languages%20into%20a%20single%20political%20project.%20Its%20finest%20leaders%20were%20not%20confined%20by%20national%20boundaries%3B%20they%20had%20universal%20vision.%20And%20they%20were%20men%20and%20women%20of%20high%20personal%20integrity.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ELeaders%20like%20Mahatma%20Gandhi%20and%20Jawaharlal%20Nehru%20made%20the%20Congress%20a%20pan-Indian%20ecumenist%20party%20transcending%20regional%2C%20linguistic%2C%20gender-based%2C%20and%20to%20some%20extent%2C%20religious%20boundaries.%20The%20post-independence%20Congress%20sought%20to%20unite%20Indians%20to%20pursue%20the%20common%20goals%20of%20economic%20development%2C%20secularism%2C%20and%20equality.%C2%A0%20The%20party%20remains%20the%20DNA%20of%20India.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBut%20the%20party%20has%20now%20declined%20into%20a%20shadow%20of%20its%20splendid%20past.%20Dynastic%20politics%20and%20its%20attendant%20sycophancy%20ruined%20the%20party%20irrecoverably.%20The%20dynasticism%20is%20deeply%20entrenched%20in%20the%20Congress%E2%80%99%20structure.%20During%20the%20Indira-era%2C%20the%20party%20was%20merely%20an%20extension%20of%20her%20will%20and%20whims.%20This%20pattern%20continued%20in%20the%20Rajiv%20and%20Sonia-eras%20too.%20Merit%20had%20been%20superseded%20by%20the%20blue%20blood%20of%20the%20reigning%20dynasty.%20Through%20the%201970s%20and%20the%201980s%2C%20the%20social%20groups%2C%20that%20were%20once%20the%20Congress%E2%80%99%20solid%20vote%20bank%2C%20started%20deserting%20the%20party%20camp.%20The%202014%20Lok%20Sabha%20election%20marked%20the%20end%20of%20the%20Congress%E2%80%99s%20umbrella%20social%20coalition%20across%20the%20country.%20The%20expanding%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eleadership%20vacuum%20further%20undermined%20the%20party%E2%80%99s%20stature.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ELack%20of%20a%20compact%20ideology%2C%20factionalism%2C%20deinstitutionalisation%20of%20the%20organisational%20machinery%2C%20and%20under-representation%20of%20backward%20castes%20and%20Dalits%20have%20been%20pointed%20out%20as%20other%20reasons%20for%20the%20party%E2%80%99s%20decline.%20The%20emergence%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eof%20regional%20parties%20with%20centrist%20ideology%20shrank%20the%20Congress%E2%80%99%20space.%20Due%20to%20these%3C%2Fspan%3E%20%3Cspan%3Efactors%2C%20election%20debacles%20became%20a%20quotidian%20affair%20and%20the%20party%E2%80%99s%20parliamentary%20strength%20grew%20weaker.%20Political%20scientist%20Suhas%20Palshikar%20rightly%20described%20the%20Congress%E2%80%99%20defeat%20in%20the%202014%20Lok%20Sabha%20election%20as%20an%20%E2%80%98electoral%20disaster%E2%80%99.%20The%20party%E2%80%99s%20tally%20nosedived%20from%20206%20in%20the%202009%20Lok%20Sabha%20election%20to%2044%20in%202014.%20The%20recent%20state%20election%20fiasco%20in%20the%20Hindi%20heartland%20has%20dealt%20a%20heavy%20blow%20to%20the%20Congress.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EThe%20Sri%20Lankan%3C%2Fb%3E%20%3Cb%3Edoppelg%C3%A4nger%C2%A0%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20Sri%20Lanka%2C%20the%20UNP%20is%20more%20akin%20to%20the%20INC%20in%20the%20historical%20context.%20The%20prototype%20of%20UNP%20was%20the%20Ceylon%20National%20Congress%20(CNC)%C2%A0%20established%20in%201918.%20Like%20the%20INC%2C%20the%20CNC%20was%20formed%20by%20the%20Westernised%20intelligentsia.%20The%20UNP%20emerged%20victorious%20in%20the%20first%20general%20election%20held%20in%201947%3B%20but%20was%20ousted%20from%20power%2C%20in%20less%20than%20a%20decade%2C%20by%20the%20Sri%20Lanka%20Freedom%20Party%20(SLFP)%20led%20by%20S.W.R.D.%20Bandaranaike.%20Both%20the%20INC%20and%20the%20UNP%20are%20ideologically%20inclined%20to%20social%20liberalism.%20The%20UNP%20has%20maintained%20an%20ideological%20and%20policy%20consistency%20as%20Sri%20Lanka%E2%80%99s%20established%20%E2%80%98centre-right%E2%80%99%20party%20as%20the%20Congress%20has%20done%20in%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20UNP%2C%20like%20the%20INC%2C%20has%20generally%20presented%20itself%20to%20minority%20communities%20like%20Tamils%20and%20Muslims%20as%20a%20more%20tolerant%20and%20liberal%20political%20alternative%20to%20the%20SLFP%20and%20the%20BJP.%20While%20the%20UNP%20and%20the%20INC%20advocate%20an%20inclusive%20plural%20secular%20politics%2C%20their%20rivals%20%E2%80%93%20the%20SLFP%20and%20the%20BJP%20%E2%80%93%20pursue%20a%3C%2Fspan%3E%20%3Cspan%3Eparochial%20ethnic%2Freligious%20nationalism.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ELike%20the%20Congress%20gradually%20lost%20its%20social%20base%2C%20the%20rise%20of%20militant%20Tamil%20nationalism%20in%20the%20late%201970s%20and%20the%20emergence%20of%20the%20Sri%20Lanka%20Muslim%20Congress%20in%20the%20mid-1980s%2C%20led%20to%20the%20UNP%E2%80%99s%20electoral%20marginalisation.%20Both%20parties%20supported%20free%20market%20economic%20policy%20and%20liberalisation%20in%20recent%20times.%20However%2C%20they%20did%20not%20hesitate%20to%20manipulate%20and%20use%20governmental%20power%20in%20an%20illiberal%20and%20draconian%20fashion%20under%20their%20dictatorial%20leaders%20like%20J.R.%20Jayewardene%20and%20Indira%20Gandhi.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ELike%20the%20INC%2C%20dyansticism%20has%20been%20a%20bane%20of%20the%20UNP.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20top%20leaders%20of%20the%20UNP%20have%20most%20often%20come%20from%20the%20extended%20wings%20of%20one%20of%20the%20two%20major%20%E2%80%98families%2Fclans%E2%80%99%20that%20have%20dominated%20Sri%20Lankan%20society%20and%20politics%20in%20the%20post-independence%20period.%20They%20have%2C%20thus%2C%20been%20selected%20on%20a%20loosely%20dynastic-nepotistic%20principle%20by%20the%20party%20elite%2C%20with%20their%20assumption%20of%20power%20legitimised%20by%20open%20popular%20elections.%20The%20founder%20of%20the%20UNP%20and%20the%20first%20prime%20minister%20of%20independent%20Ceylon%2C%20D.S.Senanayake%2C%20was%20succeeded%20by%20his%20son%20Dudley%20who%20resigned%20within%20two%20and%20half%20years%20in%201954%2C%20and%20reigns%20of%20power%20were%20taken%20up%20by%20his%20politically%20ambitious%20cousin%2C%20Sir%20John%20Kotelawala.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWith%20the%20UNP%E2%80%99s%20defeat%20in%201956%2C%20Kotelawala%20retired%20from%20politics%20to%20Britain%2C%20and%20another%20politically%20ambitious%20and%20astute%20relative%20of%20D.S.Senanayake%E2%80%99s%2C%20J.R.Jayewardene%2C%20took%20control%20of%20the%20party%20along%20with%20Dudley.%20Following%20the%20party%E2%80%99s%20defeat%20in%201994%2C%20its%20leadership%20once%20again%20devolved%20to%20Ranil%20Wickremasinghe%2C%20a%20scion%20of%20the%20powerful%20Wickremasinghe%20segment%20of%20the%20family%20and%20Jayewardene%E2%80%99s%20nephew.%20Indeed%2C%20as%20local%20political%20humour%20has%20long%20had%20it%2C%20the%20party%20was%20perhaps%20better%20called%20the%20%E2%80%98Uncle-Nephew%20Party%E2%80%99.%20Amita%20Shastri%20chronicles%20the%20dyansticism%20in%20the%20UNP%20in%20her%20essay%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EReproducing%20Hegemony%3A%20The%20United%20National%20Party%20of%20Sri%20Lanka.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20UNP%20has%20served%20as%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20ruling%20party%2C%20or%20as%20part%20of%20its%20governing%20coalition%2C%20for%2038%20of%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%2075%20years%20of%20independence.%20However%2C%20the%202020%20parliamentary%20elections%20were%20a%20catastrophe%20for%20the%20UNP.%20While%20the%C2%A0newly%20formed%20Sri%20Lanka%20Podujana%20Peramuna%C2%A0won%20a%20landslide%20victory%20with%2059.09%25%20of%20the%20votes%20and%20secured%20145%20seats%20out%20of%20a%20total%20of%20225%2C%20the%20UNP%20suffered%20its%20worst%20defeat%2C%20receiving%20only%202.15%25%20of%20votes%20cast.%20For%20the%20first%20time%2C%20it%20almost%20failed%20to%20win%20a%20single%20seat%20in%20parliament%2C%20having%20only%20gained%20one%C2%A0national%20list%20seat.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20INC%20and%20the%20UNP%2C%20like%20the%20Liberal%20Party%20in%20Britain%2C%20have%20almost%20exhausted%20their%20political%20longevity.%20But%20their%20diminution%20marks%20the%20erosion%20of%20inclusive%20pluralism%2C%20secularism%2C%20and%20liberal%20politics%20in%20South%20Asia.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cspan%3EFaisal%20C.K.%20is%20Deputy%20Law%20Secretary%20to%20the%20Government%20of%20Kerala.%20Views%20are%20personal.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1705232191000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F14143211%2FCopy-of-Copy-of-Lead-image-size-6.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fwhat-do-the-grand-old-parties-of-india-and-sri-lanka-have-in-common%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22They%20have%20been%20epitomes%20of%20the%20composite%20culture%20and%20inclusive%20pluralism%20in%20their%20respective%20countries.%20In%20the%20past%20and%20present%2C%20the%20two%20parties%20have%20been%20living%20a%20parallel%20life.%C2%A0%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fwhat-do-the-grand-old-parties-of-india-and-sri-lanka-have-in-common%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Crypto%20bulls%20think%20bitcoin%20could%20hit%20%24100%2C000%20after%20the%20SEC%20approved%20spot%20ETFs%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Garry%20Gensler%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65a00afe6979d73718227103%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221249%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ESEC%20chairman%20Gary%20Gensler%3Cp%3EDrew%20Angerer%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EThe%20SEC%20approved%2011%20spot%20bitcoin%20ETFs%20this%20week.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EThe%20cryptocurrency%20is%20up%2070%25%20since%20October%2C%20and%20bulls%20believe%20the%20watchdog's%20announcement%20could%20drive%20it%20even%20higher.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EMany%20expect%20bitcoin's%20price%20to%20pass%20six%20figures%20by%20the%20end%20of%202024.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20months%20of%20speculation%2C%20the%20Securities%20and%20Exchange%20Commission%20finally%20gave%20its%20seal%20of%20approval%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fcurrencies%2Fspot-bitcoin-etf-crypto-investing-analysis-sec-approval-gary-gensler-2024-1%5C%22%3E11%20spot%20bitcoin%20ETFs%3C%2Fa%3E%20Wednesday%20%E2%80%93%C2%A0and%20crypto%20bulls%20have%20pinpointed%20the%20regulator's%20move%20as%20a%20potential%20catalyst%20to%20push%20its%20price%20above%20six%20figures%20for%20the%20first%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUK%20bank%20Standard%20Chartered%20and%20Fundstrat%20perma-bull%20Tom%20Lee%20are%20among%20the%20names%20who%20charted%20a%20path%20for%20bitcoin%20to%20pass%20%24100%2C000%20in%20the%20run-up%20to%20the%20SEC's%20announcement%2C%20while%20other%20analysts%20called%20January%2010%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fcurrencies%2Fbitcoin-btc-etf-sec-approval-crypto-critics-reaction-regulation-investing-2024-1%5C%22%3E%26quot%3Bwatershed%20moment%26quot%3B%20and%20a%20%26quot%3B'game%20changer'%20for%20crypto%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMarket%20reaction%20has%20been%20muted%20so%20far%2C%20with%20the%20large-cap%20token%20ticking%20up%20under%201%25%20Thursday%20%E2%80%93%20but%20that%20could%20be%20a%20classic%20case%20of%20investors%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cmcmarkets.com%2Fen-gb%2Ftrading-guides%2Fbuy-the-rumour-sell-the-news%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebuying%20the%20rumor%20and%20selling%20the%20news%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B.%20Bitcoin%20has%20jumped%2070%25%20since%20late%20October%20as%20chatter%20surrounding%20the%20SEC's%20decision%20started%20to%20intensify%2C%20and%20is%20currently%20trading%20at%20its%20highest%20price%20in%20nearly%20two%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt'd%20still%20have%20to%20double%20in%20price%20again%20to%20reach%20%24100%2C000%20%E2%80%93%C2%A0but%20some%20believe%20that%20milestone%20could%20be%20reached%20by%20the%20end%20of%202024%2C%20with%20regulated%20spot%20ETFs%20likely%20to%20draw%20big-name%20institutional%20investors%20into%20the%20crypto%20space.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ESix-figure%20price%20targets%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EStandard%20Chartered%20is%20one%20high-profile%20firm%20that's%20particularly%20bullish%20on%20bitcoin.%20Earlier%20this%20month%2C%20strategists%20at%20the%20bank%20predicted%20that%20spot%20ETFs%20could%20drive%20between%20%2450%20billion%20and%20%24100%20billion%20worth%20of%20inflows%20for%20the%20token%20this%20year%20%E2%80%93%20and%20set%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fcurrencies%2Fbitcoin-price-outlook-200000-2025-inflows-spot-etf-approval-sec-2024-1%5C%22%3E%24200%2C000%20price%20target%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20the%20end%20of%202025.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20Fundstrat's%20Lee%20said%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cnbc.com%2Fvideo%2F2024%2F01%2F10%2Fwatch-cnbcs-full-interview-with-fundstrats-tom-lee.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECNBC%20interview%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20day%20the%20SEC%20announced%20its%20decision%20that%20he's%20expecting%20the%20token%20to%20climb%20to%20between%20%24100%2C000%20and%20%24150%2C000%20over%20the%20next%2012%20months%20%E2%80%93%20and%20to%20soar%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fcurrencies%2Fbitcoin-price-outlook-crypto-500000-price-target-etf-demand-boom-2024-1%5C%22%3E%24500%2C000%3C%2Fa%3E%20over%20the%20next%20five%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere's%20a%20finite%20supply%2C%20and%20now%20we%20have%20a%20potentially%20huge%20increase%20in%20demand%20with%20a%20spot%20bitcoin%20%5BETF%5D%20approval%20%E2%80%93%20so%20I%20think%20in%20five%20years%20something%20around%20half%20a%20million%20would%20be%20potentially%20achievable%2C%26quot%3B%20Lee%20told%20the%20outlet.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUniversity%20of%20Sussex%20economist%20Carol%20Alexander%2C%20who%20successfully%20called%20bitcoin's%20slump%20in%202022%20and%20surprise%20resurgence%20last%20year%2C%20isn't%20setting%20her%20sights%20so%20high%20%E2%80%93%20but%20still%20expects%20the%20cryptocurrency%20to%20be%20priced%20between%20%2470%2C000%20and%20%24100%2C000%20at%20the%20end%20of%20December.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20it's%20an%20excellent%20thing%20for%20bitcoin%20bulls%20in%20the%20short%20term%20%E2%80%94%20I've%20never%20been%20as%20bullish%20as%20this%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20told%20Business%20Insider%20in%20an%20interview%20Wednesday.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EWords%20of%20caution%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ENot%20all%20of%20the%20financial%20world%20is%20convinced%20by%20those%20lofty%20price%20targets%2C%20though.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFormer%20PIMCO%20CEO%20Mohamed%20El-Erian%20said%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Felerianm%2Fstatus%2F1745355739655188735%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epost%20on%20X%3C%2Fa%3E%20Thursday%20that%20while%20the%20SEC's%20approval%20could%20be%20a%20%26quot%3Bgame%20changer%26quot%3B%20for%20cryptocurrency%2C%20it%20wasn't%20likely%20to%20promote%20bitcoin's%20usage%20more%20widely.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAs%20notable%20as%20all%20these%20factors%20are%20for%20anchoring%20crypto%20in%20the%20investment%20world%2C%20they%20do%20not%20significantly%20propel%20its%20role%20as%20a%20potential%20global%20currency%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20wro