Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20often%20can%20feel%20like%20a%20real%20revolving%20door%2C%20but%20it's%20also%20the%20way%20to%20find%20a%20place%20to%20live%20that's%20still%20affordable%2C%20especially%20in%20a%20place%20like%20San%20Francisco%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Julia%2C%20whose%20full%20name%20and%20employment%20are%20known%20to%20Business%20Insider%2C%20but%20withheld%20over%20privacy%20concerns.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMy%20experience%20really%20was%20that%20in%20a%20lot%20of%20ways%20we%20all%20felt%20really%20held%20hostage%20by%20our%20landlords%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said%2C%20speaking%20of%20the%20dynamic%20in%20which%20renters%20put%20up%20with%20deferred%20maintenance%20and%20poor%20conditions%20because%20they%20don't%20want%20to%20be%20kicked%20out%20in%20favor%20of%20higher-paying%20tenants.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERight%20before%20the%20pandemic%2C%20Julia%20felt%20ready%20to%20leave%20the%20city%3B%20she%20moved%20into%20a%20250-square-foot%20tiny%20house%20in%20a%20former%20garage%20outside%20of%20San%20Francisco.%20She%20was%20paying%20around%20%241%2C500%20a%20month%2C%20she%20said%2C%20and%20when%20the%20pandemic%20started%20she%20and%20her%20partner%20both%20worked%20from%20home.%20But%20during%20her%20year%20and%20a%20half%20living%20there%2C%20she%20also%20began%20to%20feel%20ill.%20That's%20because%20the%20tiny%20home%20had%20some%20water%20damage%20that%20hadn't%20been%20repaired%20properly%2C%20leading%20to%20mold%20and%20health%20issues.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHere%20we%20were%20in%20a%20situation%20where%20all%20we%20could%20afford%20was%20a%20moldy%20tiny%20house%20that%20was%20making%20us%20sick.%20And%20we%20combed%20Craigslist%20and%20we%20looked%20around%20and%20yeah%2C%20there%20wasn't%20an%20option.%20It%20just%20felt%20very%2C%20very%20clear%20that%20my%20time%20in%20California%20was%20over%20and%20that%20was%20okay.%20I%20felt%20ready%20for%20a%20change%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20so%2C%20in%202021%2C%20Julia%20left%20California.%20She's%20not%20alone%3A%20Homeownership%20in%20California%20is%20becoming%20increasingly%20out%20of%20reach%20for%20millennials%2C%20and%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcalifornia-exodus-population-drops-again-political-muscle-at-risk-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estate's%20population%20has%20been%20falling%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Californians%20ages%2035%20to%2045%20have%20seen%20their%20homeownership%20rate%20fall%20precipitously%20over%20the%20last%2040%20or%20so%20years%2C%20according%20to%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fternercenter.berkeley.edu%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F05%2FHomeownership-Ladder-May-2023-Final.pdf%3Futm_source%3Dnewsletter%26utm_medium%3Demail%26utm_campaign%3Dnewsletter_axiosam%26stream%3Dtop%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Epaper%20from%20the%20Terner%20Center%20for%20Housing%20Innovation%20at%20UC%20Berkeley%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20with%20their%20homeownership%20rate%20falling%20to%2039.7%25%20in%202021%20%E2%80%94%20down%20significantly%20from%2064.4%25%20in%201980.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20might%20be%20leading%20younger%20Americans%20to%20forsake%20the%20state%20completely.%20A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmoving-from-california-pros-cons-texas-millennials-gen-z-single-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eprevious%20BI%20analysis%20found%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20the%20typical%20mover%20out%20of%20California%20was%20a%20Gen%20Zer%20or%20millennial%2C%20with%2037.9%25%20of%20movers%20in%20the%20millennial%20cohort.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJulia%20and%20her%20partner%20ended%20up%20buying%20a%20house%20in%20Santa%20Fe%2C%20New%20Mexico%2C%20in%202022%2C%20after%20making%20the%20move%20out%20there%20in%20December%202021.%20The%20median%20value%20of%20an%20owner-occupied%20home%20in%20New%20Mexico%20was%20%24243%2C100%20in%202022%2C%20compared%20to%20%24715%2C900%20in%20California%2C%20according%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdata.census.gov%2Ftable%2FACSDP1Y2022.DP04%3Fq%3Ddp04%26g%3D040XX00US06%2C35%2C48%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECensus%20Bureau's%20American%20Community%20Survey%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Even%20in%20pricier%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdata.census.gov%2Ftable%2FACSDP1Y2022.DP04%3Fq%3Ddp04%26g%3D040XX00US06%2C35%2C48_050XX00US35049%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESanta%20Fe%20County%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20median%20home%20value%20was%20%24450%2C700%20in%202022.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJulia%20and%20her%20partner%20had%20both%20independently%20been%20saving%20for%20a%20decade%20in%20hopes%20of%20being%20able%20to%20make%20a%20down%20payment%20someday.%20Even%20so%2C%20they%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Elooked%20for%20a%20house%20for%20a%20year%20during%20an%20incredibly%20competitive%20process%20%E2%80%94%20and%20were%20finally%20able%20to%20finagle%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ea%205%25%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Emortgage%20rate.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3ERates%20have%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ffred.stlouisfed.org%2Fseries%2FMORTGAGE30US%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esince%20shot%20up%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20around%206.6%25%20as%20a%20result%20of%20the%20Federal%20Reserve's%20war%20on%20inflation.%20She%20said%20that%20their%20current%20mortgage%20costs%20less%20than%20renting%20did%20in%20California.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20odds%20are%20just%20so%20stacked%20against%20younger%20first-time%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ehome%20buyers%20right%20now.%20It's%20a%20scary%20situation%20to%20see.%20I%20mean%2C%20we%20had%20to%20have%20everything%20work%20out%20absolutely%20perfectly%2C%20the%20exact%20right%20timing%20for%20it%20to%20work%20out%20for%20us%2C%26quot%3B%20Julia%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt%20was%20hard%2C%20and%20it's%20a%20little%20bit%20baffling%20to%20me%20because%20it%20shouldn't%20be%20this%20impossible%2C%20whether%20we're%20talking%20home%20ownership%20or%20finding%20a%20place%20that's%20safe%20and%20healthy%20to%20rent.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20Julia%2C%20being%20a%20homeowner%20has%20been%20a%20game%20changer%3A%20She%20started%20sleeping%20through%20the%20night%20for%20the%20first%20time%20in%20decades.%20She%20had%20no%20idea%20the%20impact%20that%20being%20in%20a%20stable%20place%20%E2%80%94%20one%20where%20they%20had%20say%20over%20the%20maintenance%20and%20repairs%20%E2%80%94%20would%20have%20on%20her%20nervous%20system.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20know%20that%20that%20sort%20of%20anxiety%20is%20something%20that%20a%20lot%20of%20people%20in%20my%20generation%20live%20with%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20would%20love%20to%20see%20more%20of%20us%20feeling%20so%20secure%20that%20we%20were%20able%20to%20sleep%20through%20the%20night%20and%20not%20worry%20so%20much%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20no%20%26quot%3Btrue%20public%20safety%20net%26quot%3B%20in%20the%20US%2C%20Julia%20said%2C%20she%20wanted%20to%20be%20sure%20that%20they%20had%20housing%20that%20would%20support%20them%20as%20they%20age.%20She's%20observed%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ethe%20difference%20between%20being%20a%20lifelong%20renter%20and%20a%20homeowner%2C%20because%20she%20watched%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ean%20elderly%20neighbor%20on%20a%20fixed%20income%20and%20a%20loved%20one%20face%20precarious%20renting%20situations.%20She%20believes%20that%20housing%20should%20be%20a%20human%20right%20%E2%80%93%20not%20a%20%26quot%3Bget%20rich%20quick%20scheme.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20feel%20very%20little%20faith%20that%20our%20current%20systems%20will%20have%20my%20back%20or%20the%20backs%20of%20more%20vulnerable%20people%20as%20we%20age%2C%20get%20sick%2C%20or%20face%20economic%20challenges%20%E2%80%94%20owning%20a%20home%20means%20I%20have%20the%20start%20of%20a%20real%20safety%20net%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BSo%20much%20more%20needs%20to%20be%20done%20at%20a%20much%20larger%20scale%20to%20protect%20people%20who%20aren't%20in%20a%20fortunate%20position%20to%20buy%20like%20we%20were.%20We%20got%20amazingly%20lucky%20on%20so%20many%20levels%2C%20but%20safe%2C%20stable%20housing%20shouldn't%20depend%20on%20having%20those%20odds.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20also%20recognizes%20that%20there's%20some%20animosity%20toward%20the%20people%20who%20move%20out%20of%20California%20into%20other%20states%2C%20especially%20as%20that%20might%20shift%20housing%20costs%20elsewhere.%20She%20also%20wishes%20people%20understood%20that%20their%20new%20Californian%20neighbors%20are%20dealing%20with%20similar%20financial%20pressures%2C%20and%20just%20trying%20to%20find%20a%20safe%20place%20to%20call%20home.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20feel%20like%20what%20happened%20was%20a%20trap%20door%20in%20the%20universe%20opened%20up%20to%20get%20us%20out%20of%20a%20situation%20where%20we%20were%20never%20going%20to%20be%20able%20to%20buy%20a%20home%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BWe%20were%20never%20going%20to%20be%20able%20to%20comfortably%20retire.%20We%20weren't%20going%20to%20be%20able%20to%20set%20up%20financial%20stability%20for%20ourselves%20in%20California.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EAre%20you%20a%20Californian%20or%20millennial%20struggling%20to%20buy%20a%20house%2C%20or%20afford%20housing%3F%20Contact%20this%20reporter%20at%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Ajkaplan%40insider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3Ejkaplan%40insider.com%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcalifornia-real-estate-moving-to-santa-fe-millennial-bought-home-2024-1%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1705231081000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65a0432edcdb354a9856d75a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcalifornia-real-estate-moving-to-santa-fe-millenn