e%20is%20done%20and%20we're%20not%20going%20back.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finflation-up-how-consumer-price-index-looked-december-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elower%20inflation%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20many%20Americans%20experience%20sticker%20shock%20when%20dining%20out.%20But%20one%20restaurateur%20warns%20that%20customers%20better%20get%20used%20to%20the%20high%20prices.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBrian%20Will%2C%20owner%20of%20Central%20City%20Tavern%20in%20the%20Atlanta%20suburb%20of%20Alpharetta%2C%20sells%20a%20BLT%20for%20%2415.95.%20While%20that%20may%20sound%20steep%20for%20a%20simple%20sandwich%2C%20he%20told%20Business%20Insider%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ea%20lot%20more%20goes%20into%20the%20price%20than%20just%20the%20cost%20of%20the%20ingredients%20and%20that%20lower%20inflation%20won't%20change%20that.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20part%20people%20don't%20understand%20is%20that%20even%20if%20inflation%20comes%20down%2C%20the%20damage%20is%20already%20done%2C%26quot%3B%20Will%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BThere%20is%20a%20misconception%20that%20if%20inflation%20drops%20from%208%25%20to%205%25%20to%203%25%20that%20prices%20come%20down.%20They%20don't.%20Inflation%20is%20a%20compounding%20issue.%20The%208%25%20increase%20is%20still%20there%2C%20as%20well%20as%20the%205%25%20increase%2C%20and%20the%203%25%20is%20added%20to%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20other%20words%2C%20lower%20inflation%20is%20not%20a%20cure.%20Rather%2C%20it%20is%20just%20a%20gauge%20of%20where%20we%20go%20in%20terms%20of%20prices%20for%20the%20future.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20a%20January%203%20interview%20with%20Stuart%20Varney%20on%20Fox%20Business'%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.foxbusiness.com%2Fvideo%2F6344219729112%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EVarney%20%26amp%3B%20Co.%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20Will%20explained%20that%20the%20ingredients%20that%20go%20into%20the%2