3EIt's%20possible%20that%20AI%2C%20working%20as%20a%20gatekeeper%2C%20will%20do%20a%20better%20job%20than%20humans%20at%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-can-older-workers-prove-ageism-and-age-bias-in-hiring-2022-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ereducing%20bias%20in%20how%20we%20get%20jobs%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20That%20could%20make%20it%20more%20likely%20that%20skills%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjob-adverts-dont-require-degree-increased-report-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Enot%20fancy%20degrees%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20connections%20%E2%80%94%20play%20a%20bigger%20role%20in%20who%20vaults%20ahead%20in%20the%20job%20market%20in%20the%20coming%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFinding%20ways%20to%20reduce%20barriers%20to%20who%20gets%20a%20fair%20shot%20at%20certain%20jobs%20is%20the%20hope%20of%20Andreas%20Leibbrandt%2C%20an%20economist%20at%20Australia's%20Monash%20University.%20He%20told%20Business%20Insider%20his%20research%20indicates%20AI%20can%20be%20more%20evenhanded%20in%20evaluating%20job%20candidates%20in%20a%20male-dominated%20field%20like%20tech%2C%20where%20men%20lean%20toward%20hiring%20other%20men.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20doesn't%20mean%20humans%20shouldn't%20make%20the%20final%20call%20about%20who%20gets%20the%20job%20offer%2C%20Leibbrandt%20said.%20He%20sees%20AI%2C%20as%20a%20tool%2C%20like%20a%20knife%3A%20%26quot%3BIf%20you%20don't%20know%20how%20to%20use%20it%2C%20you're%20going%20to%20cut%20yourself%2C%20but%20if%20you%20learn%20how%20to%20use%20it%2C%20you'll%20be%20able%20to%20make%20food%20quicker%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BThat's%20how%20I%20view%20it.%20I%20think%20it%20can%20radically%20transform%20the%20recruitment%20space.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EHelping%20tech%20bros%20be%20less%20bro-ey%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWomen%20seeking%20tech%20jobs%20seem%20to%20be%20on%20board%20with%20AI%20as%20a%20surrogate%20recruiter%2C%20according%20to%20Leibbrandt's%20research.%20%26quot%3BThe%20one%20thing%20that%20really%20pops%20out%20is%20a%20strong%20sentiment%20amongst%20women%20that%20they%20are%20confronted%20with%20bias%20when%20assessed%20by%20humans%2C%26quot%3B%20Leibbrandt%20said.%20%26quot%3BTheir%20concern%20is%20much%20less%20so%20when%20they%20are%20being%20assessed%20by%20AI.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELeibbrandt%20looked%20at%20the%20tech%20sector%20because%20anecdotal%20evidence%20from%20many%20women%20showed%20they%20experienced%20bias%20when%20going%20for%20jobs.%20And%20there%20are%2C%20he%20said%2C%20perceptions%20of%20%26quot%3Bbro%20culture%26quot%3B%20in%20that%20environment.%20The%20research%20indicates%20women%20might%20be%20onto%20something.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20do%20observe%20that%20when%20recruiters%20know%20the%20gender%20of%20the%20applicants%2C%20then%20they%20discriminate%20against%20women.%20When%20we%20remove%20the%20gender%2C%20there%20is%20no%20gender%20difference%2C%26quot%3B%20Leibbrandt%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20test%20how%20AI%20would%20handle%20job%20seekers%2C%20Leibbrandt%20and%20his%20colleagues%20placed%20ads%20for%20actual%20tech%20jobs%20and%20included%20a%20line%20that%20indicated%20that%20either%20a%20person's%20application%20would%20be%20reviewed%20by%20a%20recruiting%20team%20or%20by%20AI.%20When%20AI%20was%20in%20the%20driver's%20seat%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0at%20least%20with%20the%20initial%20screening%20of%20an%20application%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0women%20were%20more%20likely%20to%20put%20in%20an%20application.%20The%20implication%2C%20Leibbrandt%20said%2C%20was%20that%20women%20saw%20completing%20the%20application%20as%20worth%20their%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWomen%20are%20less%20likely%20to%20drop%20out%20when%20provided%20with%20information%20that%20they%20are%20being%20assessed%20by%20AI%20as%20compared%20to%20humans%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20Leibbrandt%20said%20it%20doesn't%20mean%20women%20don't%20worry%20about%20bias%20with%20AI.%20They%20just%20think%2C%20broadly%20speaking%2C%20that%20it's%20less%20of%20a%20concern%20than%20bias%20from%20people%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20the%20men%20in%20the%20experiment%2C%20Leibbrandt%20noted%2C%20the%20opposite%20happened%20when%20they%20were%20told%20their%20application%20would%20be%20scored%20by%20AI%20and%20not%20by%20a%20recruiting%20team%3A%20They%20were%20less%20likely%20to%20complete%20an%20application.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20almost%20seems%20like%20that%20a%20privilege%20has%20been%20removed%20when%20you%20have%20AI%20instead%20of%20human%20recruiters%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20referring%20to%20male%20applicants.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20other%20ways%20AI%20could%20intervene%20in%20the%20process.%20The%20tech%20could%20also%20help%20by%20scoring%20candidates'%20qualifications.%20When%20that%20happened%20in%20the%20study%2C%20male%20hiring%20managers%20didn't%20discriminate%20against%20women.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELeibbrandt%20said%20other%20research%20indicates%20that%20a%20similar%20pattern%20plays%20out%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20race.%20Those%20studies%20are%20somewhat%20constrained%20by%20small%20sample%20size%2C%20he%20noted%2C%20but%20early%20indications%20are%20that%20non-white%20women%2C%20for%20example%2C%20might%20feel%20they%20have%20a%20fairer%20shot%20at%20a%20job%20when%20AI%20does%20the%20first%20pass%20on%20a%20pile%20of%20applications.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EMaking%20it%20less%20painful%20to%20apply%20for%20a%20job%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOthers%20are%20working%20on%20ways%20AI%20could%20improve%20hiring.%20Barb%20Hyman%20is%20the%20founder%20and%20CEO%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsapia.ai%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESapia.ai%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20uses%20AI-powered%20text%20chats%20to%20screen%20job%20applicants.%20It's%20a%20departure%20from%20tools%20like%20the%20ones%20where%20an%20applicant%20records%20a%20video%20answering%20various%20questions%20or%20shows%20up%20for%20an%20in-person%20interview.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHyman%2C%20who's%20worked%20as%20a%20chief%20human%20resources%20officer%2C%20said%20an%20AI%20chat%20that's%20not%20timed%20puts%20far%20less%20pressure%20on%20people%20and%20can%20make%20it%20easier%20for%20people%20who%20might%20feel%20intimidated%20by%20a%20video%20interview%20or%20as%20though%20they're%20going%20to%20be%20passed%20over%20because%20of%20their%20background.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20differences%20between%20a%20blind%20application%20process%20versus%20something%20where%20I%20have%20to%20do%20a%20video%20or%20I%20need%20to%20show%20up%20in%20person%20is%20very%20significant%20for%20a%20large%20group%20of%20candidates%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHyman%20said%20having%20that%20initial%20screening%20done%20by%20AI%20can%20make%20it%20so%20that%20hiring%20managers%20give%20those%20candidates%20who%20make%20it%20through%20the%20process%20a%20fairer%20review.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20can't%20train%20you%20out%20of%20your%20unconscious%20biases%20because%20they're%20unconscious.%20So%20if%20the%20market%20generally%20wants%20to%20embed%20fairness%20and%20achieve%20diversity%2C%20you%20have%20to%20use%20AI%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDrawing%20in%20more%20applicants%20can%20also%20help%20employers%20that%20are%20still%20having%20trouble%20finding%20workers%20given%20the%20low%20employment%20rate%2C%20Hyman%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere's%20not%20enough%20talent%20so%20you%20have%20to%20find%20a%20more%20effective%20way%20to%20see%20talent%2C%20to%20see%20the%20potential%20in%20everyone%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-help-recruit-hire-employees-tech-women-bias-job-seeking-2024-1%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1705229221000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.ins