020%20countries%20that%20make%20up%20the%20Mediterranean.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20any%20given%20day%2C%20her%20family%20might%20enjoy%20meals%20based%20on%20cuisine%20from%20Greece%2C%20Morroco%2C%20Egypt%2C%20and%20beyond.%20But%20Karadsheh%20said%20most%20of%20her%20cooking%20is%20based%20on%20simple%2C%20accessible%20ingredients.%20Here%20are%20her%20typical%20grocery%20staples%20for%20a%20Mediterranean%20diet.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EBeans%20are%20a%20cornerstone%20of%20simple%2C%20wholesome%20recipes%20to%20boost%20longevity%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20essential%20ingredient%20in%20Karadsheh's%20pantry%20is%20something%20you%20probably%20already%20have%20at%20home%20%E2%80%94%20legumes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBeans%20have%20become%20a%20trendy%20food%2C%20according%20to%20Karadsheh%2C%20but%20have%20been%20a%20foundation%20of%20Mediterranean%20meals%20for%20centuries.%20She%20uses%20them%20in%20a%20wide%20variety%20of%20dishes%20such%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.themediterraneandish.com%2Fchickpea-salad%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Echickpea%20salad%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.themediterraneandish.com%2Fturkish-lentil-soup%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETurkish%20lentil%20soup%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETheir%20current%20popularity%20is%20in%20part%20due%20to%20the%20link%20between%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbeans-could-be-secret-for-living-longer-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebeans%20and%20longevity%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20as%20they're%20popular%20in%20regions%20called%20Blue%20Zones%20where%20people%20are%20more%20likely%20to%20live%20to%20100.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EBarley%20and%20farro%20are%20filling%20and%20rich%20in%20fiber%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhole%20grains%20are%20a%20common%20building%20block%20of%20Mediterranean%20meals%2C%20helping%20to%20provide%20a%20healthy%20source%20of%20carbohydrates%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhealth%2Fdiet-nutrition%2Ffiber-benefits%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efiber%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20key%20nutrient%20for%20digestive%20health.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKaradsheh%20said%20she%20often%20has%20barley%20and%20farro%20on%20hand%20to%20fill%20out%20soups%2C%20salads%2C%20or%20vegetable%20dishes.%20While%20it's%20not%20traditional%2C%20she%20cooks%20frequently%20with%20quinoa%20too%2C%20a%20good%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fprotein-per-serving-animal-plant-based-foods-chart-comparison-2022-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esource%20of%20plant-based%20protein%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EOlive%20oil%20is%20a%20classic%20Mediterranean%20ingredient%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EPotentially%20the%20most%20well-known%20staple%20of%20the%20Mediterranean%20diet%2C%20olive%20oil%20shows%20up%20in%20everything%20from%20dips%20and%20appetizers%20to%20entrees%20and%20even%20dessert%20or%20breakfast%20(drizzled%20over%20yogurt%20and%20boiled%20egg%20for%20a%20quick%20but%20filling%20meal).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20an%20excellent%20source%20of%20healthy%20fats%20and%20a%20good%20substitute%20for%20butter%20for%20people%20looking%20for%20a%20more%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Folive-oil-instead-of-butter-margarine-better-heart-health-2020-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eheart-healthy%20diet%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ESeasonal%20produce%20is%20a%20good%20starting%20point%20for%20delicious%2C%20healthy%20meals%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI'm%20a%20huge%20proponent%20of%20when%20you%20go%20to%20the%20grocery%20store%2C%20buying%20whatever%20is%20in%20season%2C%20if%20it's%20cauliflower%2C%20I'm%20buying%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20Karadsheh%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20of%20her%20favorites%20include%20zucchini%20in%20early%20summer%20and%20eggplant%20in%20late%20summer%20through%20the%20fall.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20staple%20veggie%20in%20Karadsheh's%20kitchen%20is%20carrots%2C%20which%20she%20often%20saut%C3%A9s%20with%20celery%20and%20onions%20to%20make%20a%20sofrito%2C%20a%20versatile%20base%20for%20building%20flavors%20in%20many%20dishes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EGreek%20yogurt%20is%20a%20versatile%20addition%20to%20savory%20dips%20and%20creamy%20dishes%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20people%20in%20the%20US%20think%20of%20having%20yogurt%20for%20breakfast%20with%20sweet%20toppings%20like%20berries%2C%20granola%2C%20or%20honey.%20But%20Karadsheh%20enjoys%20hers%20with%20with%20drizzle%20of%20olive%20oil%2C%20a%20pinch%20of%20salt%2C%20and%20a%20chopped%20boiled%20egg%20for%20a%20savory%2C%20filling%20meal.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20going%20to%20sound%20very%20weird%2C%20but%20it%20keeps%20me%20full%20throughout%20the%20morning%20because%20of%20the%20protein%2C%20and%20it's%20very%20quick%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGreek%20yogurt%20is%20also%20an%20easy%20way%20to%20add%20a%20creamy%20texture%20to%20dips%2C%20dressings%2C%20and%20sauces%20such%20as%20tzatziki.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EFrozen%20veggies%20are%20a%20convenient%20way%20to%20add%20nutrients%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20Karadsheh%20loves%20a%20good%20farmers%20market%2C%20the%20Mediterranean%20diet%20is%20all%20about%20using%20what%20you%20have%20on%20hand%2C%20and%20that%20includes%20tapping%20into%20your%20freezer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20never%20wrinkle%20my%20nose%20at%20the%20idea%20of%20using%20frozen%20ingredients%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BOn%20the%20Mediterranean%20diet%2C%20you%20really%20don't%20use%20ultra-processed%20foods%2C%20but%20that's%20not%20the%20same%20as%20a%20bag%20of%20frozen%20peas.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhealth%2Fdiet-nutrition%2Fare-frozen-vegetables-healthy%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFrozen%20vegetables%20can%20be%20just%20as%20healthy%20as%20fresh%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20as%20long%20as%20you're%20mindful%20of%20potential%20additives%20like%20sodium%2C%20a%20dietitian%20previously%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ESimple%20spices%2C%20herbs%2C%20and%20aromatics%20can%20build%20big%20flavors%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EKaradsheh%20said%20people%20shouldn't%20be%20intimidated%20by%20cooking%20Mediterranean%20food%2C%20since%20it%20doesn't%20take%20exotic%20ingredients.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20could%20make%20a%20lot%20of%20what%20I%20have%20of%20what%20I%20make%20every%20day%20with%20your%20common%20seasonings%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20few%20essentials%20include%20basic%20flavor%20enhancers%20like%20garlic%20and%20onions%2C%20as%20well%20as%20spices%20such%20as%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ecumin%2C%20coriander%2C%20paprika%2C%20turmeric%2C%20and%20cinnamon.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20latter%20may%20seem%20surprising%20as%20a%20savory%20ingredient%20to%20some%20people%2C%20but%20Karadsheh%20said%20it%20adds%20a%20warm%20flavor%20and%20pleasant%20complexity%20to%20recipes%2C%20such%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.themediterraneandish.com%2Fmeatballs-recipe-lebanese-tomato-sauce%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emeatballs%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20stew.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKaradsheh%20stocks%20up%20on%20fresh%20herbs%2C%20too.%20Parsley%20is%20a%20particular%20favorite%2C%20and%20she's%20also%20a%20fan%20of%20basil%2C%20dill%2C%20mint%2C%20and%20more.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ESalmon%20is%20a%20staple%20for%20high-protein%20meals%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20coastal%20cuisines%20of%20the%20Mediterranean%20typically%20include%20plenty%20of%20seafood%2C%20particularly%20fatty%20fish%20such%20as%20sardines.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20non-traditional%2C%20an%20approachable%20variation%20is%20salmon%2C%20which%20offers%20healthy%20omega-3%20fatty%20acids%20and%20can%20be%20ready%20for%20dinner%20in%20as%20little%20as%2015%20minutes%2C%20according%20to%20Karadsh