.%20Many%20of%20them%20though%2C%20will%20likely%20take%20on%20family%20businesses%2C%20scale%20them%2C%20or%20use%20their%20resources%20to%20pivot%20to%20another%20venture%2C%20says%20Max%20Kunkel%2C%20the%20chief%20investment%20officer%20of%20UBS's%20global%20wealth%20management%20division.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAll%20are%20almost%20certain%20to%20have%20a%20significant%20leg%20up%20over%20people%20who%20are%20less%20wealthy.%20That%20runs%20parallel%20to%20what%20economists%20say%20after%20the%20most%20difficult%20conditions%20in%20a%20century%20for%20middle%20class%20workers%20trying%20to%20build%20wealth.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20most%20clearly%20seen%20in%20the%20paychecks%20among%20people%20in%20the%20middle%20class%2C%20where%20more%20children%20are%20now%20growing%20up%20to%20earn%20less%20than%20their%20parents.%2090%25%20of%20children%20born%20in%201940%20went%20on%20to%20earn%20more%20than%20their%20parents%2C%20but%20that%20rate%20dropped%20to%20just%2050%25%20in%20the%2080s%2C%20according%20to%20data%20from%20Harvard%20University's%20Opportunity%20Insights.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20recent%20years%2C%20rates%20of%20economic%20opportunity%20have%20begun%20to%20fall%20again.%20The%20number%20of%20children%20who%20go%20on%20to%20make%20more%20than%20their%20parents%20has%20dropped%20to%20the%20lowest%20level%20since%20the%20early%201900s%2C%20according%20to%20Opportunity%20Insights%20research%20scientist%20Matthew%20Staiger.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22827%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Rates%20of%20economic%20opportunity%20have%20declined%20steadily%20since%201940%2C%20Opportunity%20Insights%20data%20shows.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65a14e616979d7371822c85b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22541%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ERates%20of%20economic%20opportunity%20have%20declined%20steadily%20since%201940%2C%20Opportunity%20Insights%20data%20shows.%3Cp%3EOpportunity%20Insights%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20chance%20of%20rising%20up%20and%20doing%20better%20than%20your%20parents%20went%20from%20basically%20%5Bcertain%5D%20for%20kids%20born%20in%20the%20mid-century%20to%20a%20coin%20flip%20in%20the%201980s%2C%26quot%3B%20Staiger%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20wealthiest%20portion%20of%20the%20population%20is%20seeing%20the%20exact%20opposite%20trend.%20A%20paper%20from%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fopportunityinsights.org%2Fnational_trends%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20Opportunity%20Insights%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20citing%20data%20from%20the%20Economic%20Policy%20Institute%20%E2%80%94%20found%20that%20in%202021%20salaries%20for%20the%20top%200.1%25%20of%20earners%20grew%20at%20the%20fastest%20pace%20of%20any%20income%20group.%20Meanwhile%2C%20the%20bottom%2090%25%20saw%20their%20wages%20decline.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwealth-inequality-housing-market-interest-rates-wage-growth-inflation-mortgage-2023-11%5C%22%3EHigher%20interest%20rates%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20other%20macroeconomic%20headwinds%20also%20mean%20that%20conditions%20for%20entrepreneurial%20wealth-building%20have%20also%20deteriorated%2C%20according%20to%20Kunkel.%20He%20says%20that's%20why%20there%20are%20fewer%20self-made%20billionaires%20today%20than%20there%20were%20in%20the%20past.%20The%20world%20minted%20just%20150%20billionaires%20in%202023%2C%20according%20to%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.forbes.com%2Fsites%2Fgigizamora%2F2023%2F04%2F04%2Fnew-billionaires-2023-jimmy-buffett-lebron-james-and-148-others-join-the-ranks-this-year%2F%3Fsh%3D2ccf6b95324d%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20Forbes'%20billionaires%20list%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20down%20from%20the%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.forbes.com%2Fbillionaires-2022%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20236%20billionaires%20that%20were%20created%20in%202022%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20trends%20of%20deepening%20inequality%20and%20narrowing%20opportunity%20could%20accelerate%20further.%20Kunkel%20expects%20interest%20rates%20to%20stay%20higher-for-longer%2C%20meaning%20wealth-building%20conditions%20for%20entrepreneurs%20could%20be%20dire%20for%20some%20time.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20the%20ranks%20of%20billionaire%20heirs%20and%20heiresses%20will%20keep%20growing.%20Kunkel%20thinks%20the%20%26quot%3BGreat%20Wealth%20Transfer%26quot%3B%20will%20stretch%20on%20over%20the%20next%2020%20to%2030%20years%2C%20with%20about%201%2C000%20billionaire%20boomers%20expected%20to%20pass%20along%20%245.2%20trillion%20to%20their%20successors.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20is%20just%20the%20first%20part%20where%20you%20can%20really%20see%20that%20it's%20starting%20to%20gain%20momentum%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20Business%20Insider.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStaiger%20also%20sees%20challenges%20in%20equaling%20out%20the%20playing%20field%20for%20self-made%20fortune%20seekers.%20Though%20things%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2F2023-year-of-the-strike-unions-sag-aftra-uaw-2023-12%5C%22%3Eunions%3C%2Fa%3E%20can%20help%20boost%20wages%20for%20lower-%20and%20middle-income%20groups%2C%20economic%20mobility%20has%20been%20on%20the%20decline%20for%20most%20of%20the%20last%2083%20years%20%E2%80%94%20meaning%20there's%20a%20lot%20of%20catching%20up%20to%20do.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20there's%20much%20work%20to%20be%20done%20to%20try%20to%20restore%20rates%20of%20economic%20opportunity%20to%20those%20observed%20several%20decades%20ago%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-become-billionaire-wealth-inequality-entrepreneurship-middle-class-inheritance-2024-1%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1705227962000%2