20or%20Burger%20King%20in%20Iceland.%20McDonald's%20Icelandic%20franchisee%20dropped%20the%20brand%20during%20the%20country's%20financial%20crisis%20in%202009%20after%20the%20collapse%20of%20the%20local%20currency%20made%20importing%20ingredients%20that%20met%20McDonald's%20quality%20standards%20too%20expensive%2C%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.visir.is%2Farticle%2F2009326438990%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EV%C3%ADsir%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20can%20still%20get%20KFC%20chicken%2C%20Domino's%20pizzas%2C%20and%20Subway%20sandwiches%2C%20though.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERetailers%20also%20sell%20a%20limited%20range%20of%20products%2C%20and%20you%20may%20struggle%20to%20find%20the%20fresh%20produce%20or%20brands%20of%20cereals%20you're%20used%20to%2C%20expats%20told%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223293%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20sign%20in%20a%20street%20in%20Reykjavik%2C%20Iceland%20advertising%20Subway%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F659c176f6979d7371821405d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223007%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EIceland%20doesn't%20have%20any%20McDonald's%2C%20Starbucks%2C%20or%20Burger%20King%20branches%2C%20but%20you%20can%20still%20go%20to%20Subway.%3Cp%3EGrace%20Dean%2FBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%3EOnly%20designated%20liquor%20shops%20sell%20alcohol%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20might%20be%20used%20to%20picking%20up%20a%20bottle%20of%20wine%20when%20you're%20grocery%20shopping%20or%20grabbing%20a%20case%20of%20beer%20on%20your%20way%20home%20from%20work.%20It's%20a%20little%20trickier%20in%20Iceland%2C%20though.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGenerally%20you%20need%20to%20go%20to%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.vinbudin.is%2Fheim%2Fum_atvr%2Fsamfelagsabyrgd-og-umhverfi%2Fnorraena-leidin%2Fnorr%25C3%25A6na-lei%25C3%25B0in.aspx%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estate-run%20liquor%20store%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20buy%20alcohol.%20Other%20Nordic%20nations%20like%20Finland%2C%20Norway%2C%20and%20Sweden%20have%20similar%20policies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThose%20in%20the%20countryside%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.vinbudin.is%2Fenglish%2Fhome%2Fopnunartimar%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehave%20limited%20opening%20hours%3C%2Fa%3E%3B%20even%20in%20the%20capital%20region%2C%20none%20are%20open%20past%208%20p.m.%20on%20Fridays.%20You%20also%20have%20to%20be%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.vinbudin.is%2Fheim%2Fum_atvr%2Fsamfelagsabyrgd-og-umhverfi%2Ftabid-2206%2Fskilr%25C3%25ADkjaeftirlit.aspx%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E20%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20buy%20alcohol%20in%20Iceland%2C%20compared%20to%2018%20in%20most%20European%20countries.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EThere%20are%20fairy%20lights%20everywhere%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20gastropub%20in%20Reykjavik%2C%20bedecked%20in%20golden%20fairy%20lights%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F659824d8ec62ab5daf8102c5%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThis%20gastropub%20in%20Reykjavik%20was%20adorned%20with%20fairy%20lights%20that%20made%20it%20look%20warm%20and%20cozy.%3Cp%3EGrace%20Dean%2FBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EHomes%20and%20businesses%20alike%20are%20adorned%20with%20fairy%20lights%20during%20the%20winter%20months%2C%20and%20they're%20a%20stark%20contrast%20to%20the%20tacky%20and%20garish%20ones%20sometimes%20spotted%20in%20the%20UK.%20Golden%20lights%20border%20windows%20and%20are%20draped%20around%20trees%20and%20hedges.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20neighborhoods%20arrange%20to%20get%20matching%20lights%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frelocated-iceland-reykjavik-brooklyn-cheaper-safer-rat-race-nyc-europe-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EJewells%20Chambers%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20an%20expat%20from%20New%20York%2C%20told%20me.%20%26quot%3BThey%20look%20really%20coordinated%20but%20also%20classier.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Strings%20of%20gold%20fairy%20lights%20on%20an%20apartment%20block%20in%20Reykjavik%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F659823c56979d7371820c131%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMany%20neighborhood%20associations%20coordinate%20which%20fairy%20lights%20they%20buy.%20This%20block%20of%20apartments%20in%20Reykjavik%20had%20matching%20lights%20on%20each%20balcony.%3Cp%3EGrace%20Dean%2FBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20it's%20dark%20for%20four%20months%20of%20the%20year%2C%20you%20just%20live%20with%20fairy%20lights%20on%20because%20you%20need%20a%20little%20bit%20more%20light%2C%20a%20little%20bit%20of%20magic%2C%26quot%3B%20Sonia%20Nicolson%2C%20who%20relocated%20from%20the%20UK%20to%20Reykjavik%2C%20told%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EI%20never%20had%20to%20pay%20extra%20for%20oat%20milk%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20caf%C3%A9s%20and%20coffee-shop%20chains%20in%20the%20UK%20offer%20non-dairy%20milk%20for%20free%2C%20but%20I'm%20accustomed%20to%20paying%20between%2030%20to%2050%20pence%20(40%20and%2065%20cents)%20extra%20to%20add%20a%20splash%20of%20oat%20milk%20to%20my%20cup%20of%20tea.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20Iceland%2C%20I%20never%20once%20spotted%20a%20caf%C3%A9%20or%20restaurant%20charging%20extra%20for%20non-dairy%20milk.%20There%20was%20usually%20a%20wide%20choice%20%E2%80%93%20almond%2C%20coconut%2C%20oat%2C%20and%20soy.%20The%20grocery%20store%20I%20visited%20had%20a%20lot%20of%20vegan%20products%2C%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIceland%20is%20surprisingly%20great%20to%20live%20in%20as%20a%20vegan%2C%26quot%3B%20Chambers%20told%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EIceland%20has%20no%20trains%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EComing%20from%20England%2C%20I'm%20very%20used%20to%20traveling%20on%20trains.%20But%20in%20Iceland%20there%2C%20quite%20simply%2C%20aren't%20any%20trains%20at%20all.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EReykjavik%20has%20a%20network%20of%20buses%2C%20though%20expats%20I%20spoke%20to%20said%20that%20driving%20is%20the%20standard%20in%20Iceland.%20Towns%20outside%20the%20capital%20region%20are%20spread%20far%20apart%2C%20but%20there%20are%20several%20domestic%20airports.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EIceland%20and%20the%20UK%20share%20a%20time%20zone%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBoth%20Iceland%20and%20the%20UK%20use%20Greenwich%20Mean%20Time%20in%20the%20winter%2C%20though%20the%20UK%20switches%20to%20British%20Summer%20Time%20in%20the%20summer%20while%20Iceland%20doesn't%20use%20daylight-saving%20time.%20I%20found%20this%20surprising%20considering%20how%20far%20west%20of%20the%20UK%20Iceland%20is.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20visited%20in%20November%2C%20the%20sun%20rose%20considerably%20later%20than%20in%20the%20UK.%20Iceland%20has%20few%20hours%20of%20daylight%20at%20the%20height%20of%20winter%2C%20and%20near-constant%20sunlight%20in%20the%20summer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224136%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20photo%20showing%20a%20street%20in%20Reykjavik%2C%20Iceland%20with%20houses%2C%20cars%20and%20a%20streetlamp.%20Though%20it%20is%20the%20morning%2C%20the%20sky%20is%20still%20a%20very%20dark%20blue%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F659c192a1c5c7b8c9a0ece77%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222068%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThis%20was%20the%20sky%20in%20Reykjavik%20at%208%3A49%20a.m.%20one%20day%20in%20mid-November.%20I%20was%20surprised%20to%20see%20it%20so%20dark%20in%20the%20mornings.%3Cp%3EGrace%20Dean%2FBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%3EA%20lot%20of%20Polish%20people%20live%20in%20Iceland%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20data%20from%20Statistics%20Iceland%2C%20more%20than%2020%25%20of%20Iceland's%20population%20was%20born%20overseas.%20The%20biggest%20group%20of%20immigrants%20comes%20from%20Poland%2C%20making%20up%20more%20than%20a%20quarter%20of%20Iceland's%20foreign-born%20population%2C%20or%20over%2023%2C000%20people%2C%20in%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20surprised%20me%20because%20I%20had%20expected%20that%2C%20based%20on%20Iceland's%20cultural%20similarities%20to%20other%20Nordic%20countries%20and%20its%20high%20living%20costs%2C%20most%20immigrants%20would%20be%20from%20wealthy%20countries%20in%20northern%20Europe.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20country%20with%20the%20second-highest%20number%20of%20immigrants%20living%20in%20Iceland%20is%20Lithuania%2C%20at%20around%204%2C000%2C%20followed%20by%20Denmark%2C%20Romania%2C%20and%20the%20US.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ficeland-first-visit-what-surprised-me-no-trains-mcdonalds-population-2024-1%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1705226821000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F659d3319ec62ab5daf81cb1f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ficeland-first-visit-what-surprised-me-no-trains-mcdonalds-population-2024-1%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Iceland's%20population%20is%20about%201%25%20the%20size%20of%20California's%2C%20and%20few%20towns%20have%20more%20than%2010%2C000%20residents.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22gdean%40businessinsider.com%20(Grace%20Dean)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ficeland-first-visit-what-surprised-me-no-trains-mcdonalds-population-2024-1%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Atlee%20shares%20video%20of%20'VD%2018'%20muhurat%20pooja%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1705226677000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-106835044%2Cimgsize-50222.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fhindi%2Fbollywood%2Fnews%2Fvd-18-atlee-gives-a-sneak-peek-at-varun-dhawan-wamiqa-gabbi-and-keerthy-sureshs-muh