s%20the%20de-facto%20US%20embassy%20in%20Taipei%20due%20to%20the%20absence%20of%20official%20diplomatic%20ties%2C%20said%20the%20delegation%20would%20include%20former%20National%20Security%20Advisor%20Stephen%20Hadley%20and%20former%20Deputy%20Secretary%20of%20State%20James%20Steinberg.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ELai%20Ching-te%20wins%20Taiwan%20election%20in%20blow%20to%20China%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAs%20we%20have%20done%20previously%20following%20a%20Taiwan%20presidential%20election%2C%20the%20US%20government%20has%20asked%20former%20senior%20officials%20to%20travel%20in%20their%20private%20capacity%20to%20Taiwan%2C%E2%80%9D%20AIT%20said%2C%20adding%20its%20US-based%20Chair%20Laura%20Rosenberger%20would%20join%20the%20officials.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9COn%20January%2015%2C%20they%20will%20meet%20with%20a%20range%20of%20leading%20political%20figures%20and%20convey%20congratulations%20from%20the%20American%20people%20to%20Taiwan%20on%20its%20successful%20elections%2C%20support%20for%20Taiwan%E2%80%99s%20continued%20prosperity%20and%20growth%2C%20and%20our%20longstanding%20interest%20in%20cross-Strait%20peace%20and%20stability.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20move%20is%20likely%20to%20irritate%20Beijing%2C%20which%20sees%20the%20island%20as%20part%20of%20China%20and%20has%20vowed%20to%20take%20back%20control%20of%20the%20self-governing%20island%2C%20with%20force%20if%20necessary.%20Similar%20visits%20in%20the%20past%20have%20prompted%20China%20to%20stage%20military%20drills%20in%20apparent%20protest.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ETaipei%20tells%20Beijing%20to%20%E2%80%98face%20reality%E2%80%99%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELai%E2%80%99s%20electoral%20victory%2C%20which%20marks%20a%20continuation%20of%20DPP%20governing%20following%20two%20terms%20under%20his%20predecessor%20Tsai%20Ing-wen%2C%20has%20been%20seen%20as%20a%20rebuff%20to%20China%E2%80%99s%20attempts%20to%20sway%20the%20vote%20in%20favour%20of%20more%20pro-Beijing%20parties.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBeijing%20has%20previously%20called%20Lai%20a%20dangerous%20separatist.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETaiwan%E2%80%99s%20Foreign%20Ministry%20called%20on%20Beijing%20to%20accept%20the%20result%20after%20voters%20gave%20Lai%20a%20comfortable%20majority.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20Ministry%20of%20Foreign%20Affairs%20calls%20on%20the%20Beijing%20authorities%20to%20respect%20the%20election%20results%2C%20face%20reality%20and%20give%20up%20suppressing%20Taiwan%20in%20order%20for%20positive%20cross-strait%20interactions%20to%20return%20to%20the%20right%20track%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20said%20in%20a%20statement.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20Beijing%20said%20Lai%E2%80%99s%20victory%20would%20not%20avert%20the%20%E2%80%9Cinevitable%20trend%20of%20China%E2%80%99s%20reunification.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChina%20also%20condemned%20a%20statement%20of%20congratulations%20from%20US%20Secretary%20of%20State%20Antony%20Blinken%20over%20Lai%E2%80%99s%20win%2C%20calling%20it%20a%20%E2%80%9Cseriously%20incorrect%20signal.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CChina%20has%20always%20firmly%20opposed%20any%20form%20of%20official%20exchanges%20between%20the%20United%20States%20and%20Taiwan%2C%20and%20resolutely%20opposes%20the%20United%20States%20interfering%20in%20Taiwan%20affairs%20in%20any%20form%20and%20under%20any%20pretext%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20Chinese%20Foreign%20Ministry%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThreat%20of%20conflict%20in%20the%20Taiwan%20Strait%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChina%20is%20Taiwan%E2%80%99s%20main%20trading%20partner%20and%20the%2064-year-old%20Lai%20said%20that%20he%20wanted%20to%20work%20with%20Beijing%20to%20maintain%20peace%20and%20stability%20in%20the%20region.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20he%20vowed%20not%20to%20cower%20to%20Chinese%20aggression%2C%20saying%2C%20%E2%80%9CWe%20are%20determined%20to%20safeguard%20Taiwan%20from%20continuing%20threats%20and%20intimidation%20from%20China.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Chinese%20Communist%20Party%20has%20become%20more%20aggressive%20in%20its%20stance%20toward%20Taiwan%20since%20the%20DPP%20came%20to%20power.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPresident-elect%20Lai%20stands%20for%20%E2%80%98the%20status%20quo%E2%80%99%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMilitary%20maneuvers%2C%20including%20both%20Chinese%20ships%20and%20jets%2C%20around%20the%20island%20have%20become%20commonplace.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20rising%20tensions%20have%20sparked%20concern%20about%20the%20prospect%20of%20an%20all-out%20war%20in%20the%20Taiwan%20Strait%20which%20would%20have%20global%20impacts.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOfficially%2C%20the%20US%20does%20not%20recognize%20Taiwan%E2%80%99s%20independence.%20However%2C%20while%20Washington%20follows%20the%20%E2%80%9COne%20China%E2%80%9D%20policy%20what%20acknowledges%20Beijing%20as%20the%20sole%20government%20of%20China%2C%20the%20US%20also%20gives%20major%20military%20support%20to%20Taiwan%20and%20opposes%20Beijing%E2%80%99s%20attempt%20to%20assert%20control.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20could%20lead%20to%20Washington%20being%20pulled%20into%20the%20conflict%20in%20case%20Beijing%20decides%20to%20attempt%20a%20military%20takeover%20of%20the%20island.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20report%20first%20appeared%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Ftaiwan-informal-us-delegation-set-to-visit-after-election%2Fa-67975592%5C%22%3EDW.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1705224319000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F14145238%2FGDyMc7Ha4AEZDC_.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Ftaiwan-anti-china-leader-wins-presidential-election-us-delegation-to-visit%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20move%20is%20likely%20to%20irritate%20Beijing%2C%20which%20sees%20the%20island%20as%20part%20of%20China%20and%20has%20vowed%20to%20take%20back%20control%20of%20the%20self-governing%20island%2C%20with%20force%20if%20necessa