ember%202023%20asked%20the%20ICJ%20to%20urgently%20issue%20provisional%20measures%20ordering%20Israel%20to%20immediately%20suspend%20its%20military%20operations%20in%20and%20against%20Gaza%20and%20to%20protect%20residents%20from%20acts%20of%20genocide%2C%20alleging%20breaches%20by%20Israel%20of%20the%201948%20Convention%20on%20the%20Prevention%20and%20Punishment%20of%20the%20Crime%20of%20Genocide%20(the%20%E2%80%9CGenocide%20Convention%E2%80%9D).%20The%20Genocide%20Convention%20defines%20genocide%20as%20%E2%80%9Cacts%20committed%20with%20intent%20to%20destroy%2C%20in%20whole%20or%20in%20part%2C%20a%20national%2C%20ethnical%2C%20racial%20or%20religious%20group%E2%80%9D.%20The%20hearings%20concerning%20the%20request%20for%20provisional%20measures%20will%20be%20held%20on%2011%20and%2012%20January%20at%20The%20Hague%2C%20in%20The%20Netherlands.%20South%20Africa%E2%80%99s%20filing%20also%20alleges%20that%20Israel%20is%20inciting%20genocide%20and%20has%20failed%20to%20prevent%20genocide.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CICJ%20decisions%20are%20final%2C%20binding%2C%20and%20not%20subject%20to%20appeal.%20Adherence%20to%20any%20order%20the%20Court%20may%20make%20by%20the%20parties%20involved%20is%20imperative%20for%20protecting%20the%20rights%20of%20Palestinians%20and%20reinforcing%20the%20primacy%20of%20international%20law%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20experts%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20commend%20South%20Africa%20for%20bringing%20this%20case%20to%20the%20ICJ%20at%20a%20time%20when%20the%20rights%20of%20Palestinians%20in%20Gaza%20are%20being%20violated%20with%20impunity.%20We%20call%20on%20all%20States%20to%20cooperate%20with%20the%20Court%20as%20it%20interprets%20the%20Genocide%20Convention%20and%20to%20respect%20the%20role%20of%20the%20ICJ%20as%20an%20independent%20court%20of%20law.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20experts%20also%20welcomed%20the%20statements%20of%20support%20by%20many%20States%20for%20South%20Africa%E2%80%99s%20action%20in%20bringing%20the%20case%20to%20the%20Court%2C%20as%20well%20as%20the%20principled%20stand%20taken%20by%20individuals%20and%20organizations%20worldwide%20that%20have%20expressed%20support%20for%20the%20submission%20of%20the%20case%20by%20South%20Africa.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20experts%20noted%20that%20this%20is%20not%20the%20first%20such%20case.%20In%202019%2C%20for%20example%2C%20The%20Gambia%20brought%20a%20case%20against%20Myanmar%20under%20the%20Genocide%20Convention%20to%20the%20ICJ%2C%20and%20asked%20for%20the%20Court%20to%20issue%20provisional%20measures%20calling%20for%20a%20halt%20to%20atrocities%20against%20the%20Rohingya%20people.%20The%20Court%20issued%20provisional%20measures%20in%20that%20case%2C%20which%20is%20still%20pending%20determination%20before%20the%20ICJ.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBoth%20South%20Africa%20and%20Israel%20have%20ratified%20the%201948%20Convention%20on%20the%20Prevention%20and%20Punishment%20of%20the%20Crime%20of%20Genocide%2C%20as%20have%20151%20other%20States.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CSouth%20Africa%E2%80%99s%20case%20has%20broader%20implications%20for%20all%20States%20%E2%80%93%20not%20only%20those%20that%20have%20ratified%20the%20Convention%20%E2%80%93%20as%20all%20are%20obligated%20both%20to%20refrain%20from%20committing%20genocide%2C%20and%20to%20prevent%20and%20punish%20it%20wherever%20it%20occurs.%20All%20States%20must%20act%20together%20to%20prevent%2C%20halt%2C%20and%20punish%20genocide%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20experts%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20ICJ%20has%20in%20the%20past%20made%20clear%20that%20obligations%20under%20the%20Genocide%20Convention%20are%20of%20an%C2%A0erga%20omnes%C2%A0nature%2C%20meaning%20that%20any%20and%20all%20countries%20have%20a%20stake%20in%20preventing%20genocide%20wherever%20it%20is%20at%20risk%20of%20occurring.%20This%20plainly%20means%20that%20uninvolved%20countries%20have%20standing%20to%20bring%20a%20case%20like%20South%20Africa%E2%80%99s%20to%20the%20ICJ%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20experts%20explained.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20its%20application%20to%20the%20Court%2C%20South%20Africa%20cited%20numerous%20statements%20by%20UN%20Special%20Procedures%20mandate%20holders%2C%20including%20the%20experts%E2%80%99%20repeated%20calls%20for%20international%20action%20to%20prevent%20genocide%20in%20Gaza.%20The%20mandate%20holders%E2%80%99%20statements%20reference%20evidence%20of%20genocidal%20incitement%20by%20Israeli%20Government%20officials%2C%20including%20a%20stated%20intent%20to%20%E2%80%9Cdestroy%20the%20Palestinian%20people%20under%20occupation%E2%80%9D%2C%20and%20calls%20for%20a%20%E2%80%9Csecond%20Nakba%E2%80%9D%20in%20Gaza%20and%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20occupied%20Palestinian%20territory.%20These%20comments%20by%20Israeli%20officials%20have%20been%20made%20amidst%20the%20extensive%20use%20by%20Israel%20of%20powerful%2C%20often%20unguided%20weaponry%20in%20Gaza%20with%20inherently%20indiscriminate%20impacts%2C%20severe%20restrictions%20on%20the%20entry%20of%20lifesaving%20humanitarian%20aid%2C%20and%20attacks%20on%20health%20care%20services%2C%20all%20of%20which%20have%20resulted%20in%20a%20devastating%20death%20toll%2C%20including%20large%20numbers%20of%20women%20and%20children%2C%20the%20forcible%20transfer%20of%20more%20than%20half%20of%20Gaza%E2%80%99s%20population%2C%20and%20extensive%20destruction%20of%20life-sustaining%20infrastructure.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERecalling%20the%20alarming%20magnitude%20and%20intensity%20of%20the%20bombardments%2C%20the%20experts%20also%20reiterated%20their%20demand%2C%20issued%20in%20December%202023%20along%20with%20other%20Special%20Procedure%20mandate%20holders%2C%20for%20an%20immediate%20ceasefire%20and%20a%20halt%20to%20displacement%2C%20domicide%2C%20and%20attacks%20on%20health%20infrastructure.%20The%20experts%20further%20called%20for%20immediate%20action%20to%20ensure%20the%20unimpeded%20delivery%20of%20desperately%20needed%20humanitarian%20aid%20to%20people%20in%20Gaza%2C%20especially%20for%20the%20sick%20or%20injured%2C%20persons%20with%20disabilities%2C%20older%20persons%2C%20pregnant%20women%2C%20and%20children.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E*The%20experts%3A%C2%A0Ms.%20Margaret%20Satterthwaite%2C%C2%A0%3Ca%20title%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ohchr.org%2Fen%2Fspecial-procedures%2Fsr-independence-of-judges-and-lawyers%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ohchr.org%2Fen%2Fspecial-procedures%2Fsr-independence-of-judges-and-lawyers%5C%22%3ESpecial%20Rapporteur%20on%20the%20independence%20of%20judges%20and%20lawyers%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%C2%A0Ms.%20Francesca%20Albanese%2C%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ohchr.org%2Fen%2Fspecial-procedures%2Fsr-palestine%5C%22%3ESpecial%20Rapporteur%20on%20the%20situation%20of%20human%20rights%20in%20the%20Palestinian%20Territory%20occupied%20since%201967%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%C2%A0Ms.%20Siobh%C3%A1n%20Mullally%2C%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ohchr.org%2Fen%2Fspecial-procedures%2Fsr-trafficking-in-persons%5C%22%3ESpecial%20Rapporteur%20on%20trafficking%20in%20persons%2C%20especially%20women%20and%20children%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ohchr.org%2Fen%2Fspecial-procedures%2Fsr-slavery%2Fannual-thematic-reports%5C%22%3ETomoya%20Obokata%2C%C2%A0Special%20Rapporteur%20on%20contemporary%20forms%20of%20slavery%2C%20including%20its%20causes%20and%20consequences%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%C2%A0Mr.%20Livingstone%20Sewanyana%2C%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Funitednations.sharepoint.com%2Fen%2Fspecial-procedures%2Fie-international-order%5C%22%3EIndependent%20Expert%20on%20the%20promotion%20of%20a%20democratic%20and%20equitable%20international%20order%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%C2%A0Mr.%20Ben%20Saul%2C%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ohchr.org%2Fen%2Fspecial-procedures%2Fsr-terrorism%23%253a~%253atext%3DAt%2520its%2520thirty-fifth%2520session%252coffice%2520on%25201%2520August%25202017.%5C%22%3ESpecial%20Rapporteur%20on%20the%20promotion%20and%20protection%20of%20human%20rights%20and%20fundamental%20freedoms%20while%20countering%20terrorism%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%C2%A0Ms.%2