hips%20came%20to%20light%20at%20his%20funeral%2C%20attended%20by%20luminaries%20spanning%20political%20and%20corporate%20realms.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EREAD%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20%7C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fmilind-deora-quits-congress-says-ending-my-familys-55-year-relationship-with-the-party-4859360%5C%22%3EMilind%20Deora%20Quits%20Congress%20Ahead%20Of%20Polls%20To%20%26quot%3BWalk%20On%20Path%20Of%20Development%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20addition%20to%20being%20the%20president%20of%20the%20Mumbai%20Regional%20Congress%20Committee%20for%20an%20impressive%2022-year%20stint%2C%20Murli%20Deora%20was%20also%20a%20four-time%20Lok%20Sabha%20MP%20and%20three-time%20Rajya%20Sabha%20MP.%20He%20also%20stands%20singular%20as%20the%20only%20petroleum%20minister%20to%20serve%20a%20full%20five-year%20term%20in%20two%20consecutive%20governments%20under%20prime%20minister%20Manmohan%20Singh.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%201968%2C%20a%20payment%20of%2025%20paise%20secured%20his%20position%20as%20a%20primary%20member%20of%20the%20Congress%2C%20a%20party%20to%20which%20he%20remained%20steadfastly%20loyal%20throughout%20his%20career.%20His%20early%20foray%20into%20municipal%20politics%20marked%20the%20beginning%20of%20a%20journey%20that%20would%20see%20him%20serve%20as%20Mumbai's%20mayor%20and%20eventually%20shape%20the%20political%20landscape%20of%20South%20Mumbai.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%201970s%2C%20when%20Congress%20faced%20setbacks%20both%20at%20the%20national%20and%20state%20levels%2C%20Mr%20Deora%20emerged%20as%20a%20key%20figure.%20A%20split%20engineered%20by%20Sharad%20Pawar%2C%20leading%20to%20the%20formation%20of%20the%20Progressive%20Democratic%20Front%20with%20the%20Janata%20Party%2C%20marked%20a%20challenging%20period%20for%20Congress.%20Despite%20having%20no%20aspirations%20for%20ministerial%20roles%2C%20Murli%20Deora%20assumed%20the%20role%20of%20president%20of%20the%20Bombay%20Pradesh%20Congress%20Committee%2C%20a%20position%20he%20held%20for%20over%20two%20decades.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Congress%20veteran%20was%20also%20a%20close%20confidant%20of%20prime%20minister%20Rajiv%20Gandhi.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-01%2Fmvtseahg_murli-deora-rajiv-gandhi_625x300_14_January_24.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETasked%20with%20the%20role%20of%20a%20bridge%20between%20the%20Congress%20and%20the%20city's%20corporate%20elite%2C%20he%20facilitated%20the%20smooth%20flow%20of%20funds%20to%20the%20party.%20His%20relationships%20with%20industrial%20magnates%20like%20the%20Birlas%20and%20Dhirubhai%20Ambani%20played%20a%20crucial%20role%20in%20sustaining%20the%20party's%20financial%20machinery.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhenever%20Sonia%20Gandhi%20visited%20Mumbai%2C%20Murli%20Deora%20organised%20lunches%20at%20the%20Cricket%20Club%20of%20India%2C%20an%20event%20that%20drew%20journalists%20and%20prominent%20personalities%20alike.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%2021st%20century%2C%20the%20baton%20of%20South%20Mumbai's%20representation%20was%20passed%20on%20to%20his%20son%2C%20Milind%2C%20as%20the%20senior%20Deora%20continued%20to%20exert%20influence%20behind%20the%20scenes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECongress%20leader%20Jairam%20Ramesh's%20today%20described%20Murli%20Deora%20as%20a%20stalwart%20Congressman%20who%20stood%20by%20the%20party%20through%20thick%20and%20thin.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EMilind%20Deora's%20Exit%2C%20And%20Its%20Impact%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20tributes%20flowed%2C%20the%20departure%20of%20Milind%20Deora%20from%20the%20Congress%20has%20raised%20questions%20on%20how%20the%20move%20could%20affect%20the%20party.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Congress%2C%20a%20member%20of%20the%20opposition%20INDIA%20bloc%2C%20is%20already%20in%20a%20ti