gress-report-on-katrina-kaifs-film-4860134%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Every%20Fingerprint%20Is%20Not%20Unique%2C%20Reveals%20New%20AI%20Study%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EWe%20have%20always%20heard%20that%20each%20fingerprint%20on%20a%20person's%20hand%20is%20unique.%20However%2C%20this%20theory%20is%20currently%20being%20contested%20by%20a%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.engineering.columbia.edu%2Fnews%2Fai-discovers-not-every-fingerprint-unique%5C%22%3E%20Columbia%20University%20study%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Recently%2C%20an%20artificial%20intelligence%20program%20was%20trained%20by%20a%20team%20at%20a%20US%20university%20to%20analyse%2060%2C000%20fingerprints%20in%20an%20attempt%20to%20determine%20which%20ones%20belonged%20to%20the%20same%20person.%20According%20to%20the%20researchers%2C%20the%20system%20can%20determine%20if%20fingerprints%20belong%20to%20a%20single%20individual%20with%2075-90%20per%20cent%20accuracy%2C%20as%20per%20a%20report%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fedition.cnn.com%2F2024%2F01%2F12%2Fworld%2Ffingerprints-ai-based-study-scn%2Findex.html%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3ECNN%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGabe%20Gua%2C%20an%20undergraduate%20student%20in%20Columbia's%20computer%20science%20programme%2C%20oversaw%20a%20research%20team%20on%20the%20topic%2C%20with%20University%20of%20Buffalo%20professor%20Wenyao%20Xu%20serving%20as%20one%20of%20his%20co-authors.%20Published%20this%20week%20in%20the%20journal%20Science%20Advances%2C%20the%20report%20seemingly%20upends%20a%20long-accepted%20fact%20about%20fingerprints.%20The%20scientists%20used%20an%20AI%20model%20known%20as%20a%20deep%20contrastive%20network%2C%20which%20is%20frequently%20used%20for%20tasks%20like%20face%20recognition%2C%20to%20arrive%20at%20the%20study's%20conclusions.%20After%20giving%20it%20their%20spin%2C%20the%20researchers%20fed%20the%20data%20from%20the%20US%20government%20database%20in%20pairs%2C%20some%20of%20which%20came%20from%20the%20same%20individual%20(but%20on%20different%20fingers)%20and%20others%20from%20different%20persons.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20then%20discovered%20that%20fingerprints%20from%20different%20fingers%20on%20the%20same%20person%20had%20significant%20similarities.%20As%20a%20result%2C%20it%20was%20able%20to%20distinguish%20between%20fingerprints%20belonging%20to%20the%20same%20person%20and%20those%20that%20weren't%2C%20with%20a%20single%20pair's%20accuracy%20peaking%20at%2077%20per%20cent%2C%20seemingly%20refuting%20the%20idea%20that%20each%20fingerprint%20is%20distinctive.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMr%20Guo%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BWe%20found%20a%20rigorous%20explanation%20for%20why%20this%20is%20the%20case%3A%20the%20angles%20and%20curvatures%20at%20the%20centre%20of%20the%20fingerprint.%26quot%3B%20%C2%A0The%20researchers%20believe%20that%20the%20AI%20tool%20analysed%20the%20fingerprints%20differently%20than%20conventional%20techniques%2C%20emphasising%20the%20direction%20of%20the%20ridges%20in%20the%20middle%20of%20the%20finger%20rather%20than%20minutiae-the%20places%20where%20individual%20ridges%20stop%20and%20split.%20%26quot%3BThey%20are%20great%20for%20fingerprint%20matching%2C%20but%20not%20reliable%20for%20finding%20correlations%20among%20fingerprints%20from%20the%20same%20person.%20And%20that's%20the%20insight%20we%20had%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20authors%20acknowledged%20that%20there%20could%20be%20biases%20in%20the%20data.%20The%20study%20added%20that%20even%20while%20they%20think%20the%20AI%20system%20functions%20mostly%20the%20same%20for%20both%20racial%20and%20gender%20identities%2C%20more%20thorough%20research%20of%20a%20more%20comprehensive%20collection%20of%20fingerprints%20is%20necessary%20before%20the%20technology%20can%20be%20used%20in%20real%20forensics.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20most%20immediate%20application%20is%20it%20can%20help%20generate%20new%20leads%20for%20cold%20cases%2C%20where%20the%20fingerprints%20left%20at%20the%20