ah%20Mosque%20in%20Mathura.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20frenzied%20mob%20of%20politically-motivated%20%E2%80%98karsevaks%E2%80%99%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fayodhyatimeline%23%3A~%3Atext%3DThe%2520Babri%2520Masjid%2520is%2520constructed%2Cwas%2520the%2520birthplace%2520of%2520Rama.%5C%22%3Edemolished%20the%20Babri%20Masjid%20in%20Ayodhya%20on%20December%206%2C%201992%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20after%20a%20long-drawn%20political%20movement%20led%20by%20the%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%20and%20its%20ideological%20fountainhead%2C%20the%20Rashtriya%20Swayamsevak%20Sangh.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20August%205%2C%202019%2C%2028%20years%20after%20the%20mosque%20was%20razed%20to%20the%20ground%20in%20full%20public%20view%2C%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20formally%20launched%20the%20construction%20of%20a%20Supreme%20Court-approved%20Ram%20Temple%20at%20the%20spot%20where%20it%20is%20believed%20the%20deity%20Ram%20was%20born.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20much%20of%20the%20brouhaha%20has%20been%20concentrated%20on%20the%20January%2022%20%3Cem%3E%E2%80%98pran%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Cem%3Epratishtha%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%99%20or%20consecration%20ceremony%20of%20the%20temple%2C%20which%20Modi%20will%20preside%20over%2C%20the%20matter%20listed%20around%20the%20date%20in%20different%20courts%20hold%20significance%20in%20Hindutva%20parties%E2%80%99%20legal%20battle%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcommunalism%2Fkashi-mathura-baaki-hain-why-the-ayodhya-verdict-wont-offer-any-respite-from-saffron-hatred%5C%22%3Eclaim%20the%20other%20two%20mosques%20in%20Varanasi%20and%20Mathura%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Allahabad%20high%20court%20has%20listed%20January%2017%20as%20the%20date%20for%20argument%20on%20the%20composition%20and%20modalities%20of%20an%20advocate%20commission%20to%20survey%20the%20Shahi%20Idgah%20Mosque%20after%20Hindu%20plaintiffs%20claimed%20that%20there%20were%20signs%20of%20Hindu%20religion%20on%20its%20structure.%20On%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20a%20local%20court%20in%20Varanasi%20is%20on%20January%2024%20to%20decide%20whether%20the%20report%20of%20a%20scientific%20survey%20of%20the%20Gyanvapi%20Masjid%20conducted%20by%20the%20Archaeological%20Survey%20of%20India%20would%20be%20made%20public%20or%20not.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20January%2011%2C%20the%20Allahabad%20high%20court%20decided%20to%20consolidate%2015%20out%20of%20the%2018%20suits%20filed%20in%20the%20Mathura%20matter%2C%20where%20Hindu%20plaintiffs%20have%20prayed%20for%20the%20removal%20of%20the%20Mughal-era%20Shahi%20Idgah%20Mosque.%20Justice%20Mayank%20Kumar%20Jain%20passed%20the%20order%2C%20saying%20that%20the%20relief%20claimed%20in%20these%2015%20suits%20numbered%201%2C%202%2C%204%2C%205%2C%206%2C%207%2C%208%2C%209%2C%2011%2C%2012%2C%2013%2C%2014%2C%2015%2C%2016%20and%2018%20were%20similar.%20The%20judge%20said%20the%20proceedings%20in%20these%20suits%20may%20be%20decided%20simultaneously%20on%20the%20basis%20of%20common%20evidence.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CTo%20save%20the%20time%20of%20the%20court%2C%20the%20expenses%20to%20be%20incurred%20to%20the%20parties%2C%20and%20to%20avoid%20conflicting%20judgments%20it%20appears%20expedient%20in%20the%20interest%20of%20justice%20to%20consolidate%20the%20suits%20with%20each%20other%2C%E2%80%9D%20Justice%20Jain%20observed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20court%20made%20the%20suit%20titled%20%E2%80%98%3Cem%3EBhagwan%20Shri%20Krishan%20Virajman%20at%20Katra%20Keshav%20Dev%20Khewat%20No.%20255%20and%20others%20Vs.%20U.P.%20Sunni%20Central%20Waqf%20Board%20through%20Chairman%20and%20others%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%99%2C%20as%20the%20leading%20case.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20379px)%2085vw%2C%20379px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F14104324%2Fdownload-1-1.jpeg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22379%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F14104324%2Fdownload-1-1.jpeg%20225w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F14104324%2Fdownload-1-1-150x150.jpeg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-692888%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22379%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EHari%20Shankar%20Jain.%20Photo%3A%20LinkedIn%2Fhari-shankar-jain-548a42145%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20case%20is%20being%20argued%20by%20pro-Hindutva%20lawyer%20Hari%20Shankar%20Jain%2C%20who%20was%20involved%20in%20both%20the%20Babri%20Masjid%20and%20Gyanvapi%20Masjid%20cases%20and%20was%20in%202014%20felicitated%20by%20the%20BJP%20for%20filing%20cases%20against%20the%20then%20Samajwadi%20Party-led%20Uttar%20Pradesh%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20December%2014%2C%20the%20court%20had%20allowed%20the%20application%20of%20the%20Hindu%20side%20to%20appoint%20an%20advocate%20commission%20to%20survey%20the%20Shahi%20Idgah%20Masjid%20adjoining%20the%20Krishna%20Janmabhoomi%20Temple.%20However%2C%20the%20composition%20and%20modalities%20of%20the%20commission%20are%20yet%20to%20be%20settled%20by%20court%20and%20it%20is%20expected%20to%20do%20it%20on%20January%2017.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20court%20on%20December%2014%20observed%20that%20by%20appointment%20of%20a%20panel%20of%20three%20advocates%20as%20commission%2C%20neither%20side%20would%20suffer%20any%20harm%20or%20injury%2C%20as%20the%20commissioner%20report%20does%20not%20affect%20the%20merits%20of%20the%20case.%20During%20the%20course%20of%20the%20survey%2C%20the%20%E2%80%9Csanctity%20of%20the%20campus%20can%20be%20directed%20to%20be%20maintained%20strictly%E2%80%9D%20and%20that%20no%20harm%20or%20injury%20be%20caused%20to%20the%20structure%20in%20any%20manner%2C%20the%20judge%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20commission%20would%20also%20submit%20its%20report%20on%20the%20alleged%20existence%20of%20particular%20Hindu%20signs%20in%20the%20mosque%2C%20as%20alleged%20by%20the%20Hindu%20plaintiffs.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20plaintiffs%20have%20claimed%20that%20the%20place%20of%20birthplace%20of%20Krishna%20lies%20beneath%20the%20mosque%20and%20that%20there%20were%20a%20%E2%80%9Cnumber%20of%20signs%E2%80%9D%20that%20established%20that%20the%20structure%20of%20the%20mosque%20was%20a%20Hindu%20temple.%20The%20Hindu%20plaintiffs%20submitted%20the%20following%20in%20court%3A%20the%20kalash%20and%20pinnacle%20at%20the%20top%20of%20the%20mosque%20exemplify%20Hindu%20architectural%20style%20and%20are%20not%20present%20in%20any%20Islamic%20structure%3B%20a%20pillar%20with%20a%20lotus%20shaped%20top%2C%20a%20characteristic%20of%20Hindu%20temples%2C%20exists%20above%20the%20main%20gate%20of%20the%20mosque%3B%20the%20image%20of%20Hindu%20deity%20Sheshnaag%2C%20who%20Hindus%20believe%20protected%20Krishna%20on%20the%20night%20of%20his%20birth%2C%20is%20etched%20on%20the%20wall%20of%20the%20structure%3B%20%C2%A0there%20are%20visible%20Hindu%20religious%20symbols%20and%20engravings%20at%20the%20base%20of%20the%20pillar%20of%20the%20mosque.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Muslim%20side%20led%20by%20the%20UP%20Sunni%20Central%20Waqf%20Board%20dismissed%20these%20claims%20arguing%20that%20the%20Shahi%20Idgah%20Mosque%20does%20not%20fall%20within%20the%20ambit%20of%20the%2013.37%20acres%20land%20at%20Katra%20Keshav%20Dev%20and%20that%20the%20birth%20place%20of%20Lord%20Krishna%20does%20not%20lie%20beneath%20the%20mosque.%20They%20categorically%20denied%20that%20designs%20in%20Mughal%20architecture%20resemble%20Hindu%20religious%20symbols%20or%20establish%20that%20the%20Shahi%20Idgah%20Mosque%20was%20a%20temple.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F25112937%2FSEM1.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F25112937%2FSEM1.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F25112937%2FSEM1-300x169.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F25112937%2FSEM1-1024x577.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-674675%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22676%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EThe%20Shahi%20Eidgah%20Masjid%20and%20the%20Shri%20Krishna%20Janmasthan%20temple%20in%20Mathura.%20Photo%3A%20Tarushi%20Aswani%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESubmitting%20that%20the%20claim%20of%20the%20Hindu%20plaintiffs%20was%20based%20on%20%E2%80%9Cguess%20work%E2%80%9D%20and%20was%20%E2%80%9Cnot%20substantiated%20by%20any%20documentary%20evidence%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20Muslim%20side%2C%20while%20objecting%20to%20a%20commission%20survey%2C%20said%20the%20%E2%80%9Ccourt%20cannot%20be%20made%20a%20tool%20to%20collect%20evidence%20for%E2%80%9D%20the%20plaintiffs.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20HC%20overruled%20these%20arguments%20to%20allow%20for%20a%20survey.%20Following%20the%20court%20order%2C%20counsel%20for%20the%20Hindu%20plaintiffs%20Vishnu%20Shankar%20Jain%20submitted%20an%20application%20pleading%20that%20the%20commission%20may%20be%20headed%20by%20a%20retired%20High%20Court%20judge%20and%20that%20certain%20advocates%20on%20their%20behalf%20may%20also%20be%20permitted%20to%20participate%20in%20the%20proceedings%20of%20the%20commission.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20significant%20development%20is%20also%20expected%20in%20the%20matter%20of%20the%20Gyanvapi%20Masjid%20adjacent%20to%20the%20Kashi%20Vishwanath%20Temple%20in%20Varanasi.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Archaeological%20Survey%20of%20India%20on%20December%2018%20submitted%20in%20%C2%A0a%20sealed%20cover%20its%20report%20of%20a%20scientific%20survey%20of%20the%20Gyanvapi%20Masjid%20premises%20in%20a%20Varanasi%20district%20court.%C2%A0The%20ASI%C2%A0carried%C2%A0out%20a%20scientific%20survey%20of%20the%2017th%20century%20mosque%20to%20determine%20if%20it%20was%20constructed%20over%20a%20pre-existing%20structure%20of%20a%20temple%2C%20as%20claimed%20by%20Hindu%20petitioners.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Varanasi%20district%20court%20is%20on%20January%2024%20expected%20to%20decide%20if%20the%20ASI%20survey%20report%20would%20be%20made%20public%20or%20its%20copies%20provided%20to%20the%20two%20sides.%20The%20ASI%20had%20last%20week%20urged%20the%20district%20judge%20to%20not%20make%20its%20report%20public%20for%20another%20four%20weeks%20citing%20the%20December%2019%20judgment%20by%20the%20Allahabad%20High%20Court%20in%20which%20it%20had%20dismissed%20several%20pleas%20of%20the%20UP%20Sunni%20Central%20Waqf%20Board%20and%20the%20masjid%20committee%20challenging%20the%20maintainability%20of%20a%20suit%20seeking%20restoration%20of%20a%20temple%20at%20the%20site%20of%20the%20Gyanvapi%20Masjid.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20dispute%20raised%20in%20the%20suit%20is%20of%20vital%20national%20importance.%20It%20is%20not%20a%20suit%20between%20the%20two%20individual%20parties.%20It%20affects%20two%20major%20communities%20of%20the%20country%2C%E2%80%9D%20Justice%20Rohit%20Ranjan%20Agarwal%20said%20as%20he%20set%20a%20six-month%20deadline%20for%20the%20completion%20of%20proceedings%20in%20a%20Varanasi%20court%20in%20the%201991%20suit.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20HC%20ruled%20that%20the%20original%20suit%20of%201991%20was%20not%20barred%20by%20provisions%20of%20The%20Places%20of%20Worship%20(Special%20Provisions)%20Act%2C%201991.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fwhy-the-places-of-worship-act-must-be-preserved%23%3A~%3Atext%3DThe%2520Places%2520of%2520Worship%2520Bill%2Cnext%2520to%2520the%2520Babri%2520Masjid.%5C%22%3EWhy%20the%20Places%20of%20Worship%20Act%20Must%20Be%20Preserved%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20original%20suit%20of%201991%20was%20filed%20by%20the%20Hindu%20plaintiffs%20seeking%20possession%20of%20the%20Gyanvapi%20Masjid%20premises.%20The%20recent%20suit%20filed%20by%20five%20Hindu%20women%20led%20by%20Rakhi%20Singh%20seeks%20year-round%20access%20for%20%3Cem%3Edarshan%3C%2Fem%3E%20and%20%3Cem%3Epooja%3C%2Fem%3E%20of%20Maa%20Shringar%20Gauri%20in%20the%20Gyanvapi%20Masjid%20compound.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20HC%20on%20December%2019%20also%20directed%20the%20ASI%20to%20submit%20its%20scientific%20survey%20report%20in%20the%201991%20suit%20currently%20heard%20in%20the%20court%20of%20civil%20judge%20senior%20division%2C%20fast%20track.%20In%20case%20it%20was%20found%20that%20%E2%80%9Cfurther%20survey%20is%20required%2C%20which%20have%20been%20left%20out%20in%20the%20survey%20conducted%20by%20ASI%2C%20the%20Court%20below%20shall%20issue%20necessary%20directions%E2%80%9D%20to%20carry%20out%20further%20survey%20in%20view%20of%20order%20dated%20April%208%2C%202021%2C%20the%20HC%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20matter%20is%20listed%20in%20the%20civil%20judge%20court%20on%20January%2019.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20January%203%2C%20the%20ASI%2C%20in%20an%20application%20submitted%20to%20the%20district%20court%2C%20argued%20that%20its%20report%20was%20of%20%E2%80%9Cvital%20importance.%E2%80%9D%20If%20the%20report%20%E2%80%9Cis%20unsealed%20and%20disclosed%20in%20public%E2%80%9D%20before%20the%20submission%20of%20a%20copy%20of%20the%20report%20in%20the%20suit%20of%20the%20%E2%80%98Ancient%20Idol%20of%20Swambhu%20Lord%20Vishweshwar%20vs%20Anjuman%20Intezamia%20Masajid%20in%20the%20civil%20judge%2C%20senior%20division%2C%20fast%20track%2C%20there%20would%20be%20%E2%80%9Cmore%20chance%E2%80%9D%20of%20spreading%20%E2%80%9Crumour%20and%20misrepresentation%20in%20public%2C%E2%80%9D%20which%20may%20affect%20the%20work%20of%20the%20ASI%2C%20the%20ASI%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Allahabad%20HC%20had%20in%20August%202023%20paved%20the%20way%20for%20conducting%20a%20scientific%20survey%20of%20the%C2%A0Gyanvapi%C2%A0Masjid%20after%20it%20dismissed%20the%C2%A0Gyanvapi%C2%A0mosque%20committee%E2%80%99s%20petition%20challenging%20the%20Varanasi%20district%20judge%E2%80%99s%20July%2021%20order%20for%20a%20survey%20of%20the%20premises%20by%20the%C2%A0ASI.%20The%C2%A0district%20judge%20had%20in%20July%20directed%20the%C2%A0ASI%C2%A0Director%20to%20undertake%20scientific%20investigation%2C%20survey%20or%20excavation%20at%20the%20site%2C%20i.e%20settlement%20plot%20no%209130%2C%20excluding%20the%20areas%20(the%20ablution%20tank)%20sealed%20by%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20last%20year.%20The%20district%20court%20had%20also%20directed%20the%C2%A0ASI%C2%A0to%20conduct%20a%20detailed%20scientific%20investigation%20by%20using%20GPR%20Survey%2C%20excavation%2C%20dating%20method%20and%20other%20modern%20techniques%20of%20the%20present%20structure%20to%20find%20out%20whether%20it%20had%20been%20constructed%20over%20a%20pre-existing%20structure%20of%20Hindu%20temple.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20September%2C%20the%20district%20judge%C2%A0directed%20the%20ASI%C2%A0to%C2%A0collect%20all%20the%20objects%20and%20materials%2C%20including%20those%20linked%20to%20the%20Hindu%20religion%2C%20found%20during%20its%20scientific%20survey%20of%20the%20Gyanvapi%20Masjid%20premises%20and%20submit%20it%20to%20the%20district%20administration.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1705213859000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2019%2F10%2F20121648%2FScreen-Shot-2019-10-20-at-12.16.28-PM.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcommunalism%2Fayodhya-mathura-varanasi-why-the-coming-week-is-crucial-for-the-hindutva-project%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Legal%20developments%20are%20also%20expected%20to%20have%20a%20bearing%20on%20the%20fate%20of%20the%20other%20two%20mosques%20claimed%20by%20the%20Sangh%20Parivar-led%20Hindutva%20parties.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcommunalism%2Fayodhya-mathura-varanasi-why-the-coming-week-is-crucial-for-the-hindutva-project%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22amp