Fnews%2Fprime-video-southeast-asia-singapore-staff-cut-1235871006%2Famp%2F%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Over%20Time%2C%20Discrimination%20May%20Have%20Come%20to%20Explain%20More%20of%20the%20Indian%20Gender%20Wage%20Gap%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F13200128%2FWorkplace.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20India%2C%20the%20process%20of%20structural%20transformation%20has%20resulted%20in%20a%20large%20change%20in%20the%20composition%20of%20the%20female%20workforce.%20Older%2C%20less%20educated%20women%20have%20exited%20while%20younger%2C%20more%20educated%20women%20have%20entered.%20The%20former%20have%20received%20much%20more%20attention%20in%20the%20form%20of%20the%20debate%20over%20declining%20female%20labour%20force%20participation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%201983%2C%20about%2033%25%20of%20working-age%20rural%20women%20were%20in%20paid%20employment.%20By%202017%2C%20this%20had%20fallen%20to%20about%2020%25.%20Employment%20rates%20have%20since%20risen%20for%20women%20in%20rural%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20second%20aspect%20of%20the%20compositional%20shift%20is%20also%20equally%20significant%2C%20manifested%20in%20the%20rising%20share%20of%20women%20in%20salaried%20employment%20accompanied%20by%20a%20declining%20share%20of%20women%20in%20casual%20wage%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESelected%20findings%20from%20the%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcse.azimpremjiuniversity.edu.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2FState_of_Working_India_2023_ebook_revised.pdf%5C%22%3EState%20of%20Working%20India%20Report%202023%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0focus%20on%20the%20implications%20of%20this%20fact%20on%20women%E2%80%99s%20earnings%20and%20the%20gender-based%20earnings%20gap%20using%20evidence%20from%20official%20employment%20surveys.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EEarnings%20gap%20across%20employment%20types%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20compositional%20shift%20away%20from%20casual%20wage%20work%20toward%20regular%20wage%20employment%20narrows%20the%20gender%20earnings%20gap%20because%20the%20gap%20tends%20to%20be%20larger%20in%20the%20former.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202021-22%2C%20the%20average%20monthly%20earnings%20of%20a%20regular%20salaried%20man%20was%20approximately%20Rs.%2017%2C910.%20A%20salaried%20woman%20earned%20about%20Rs.%2013%2C666.%20In%20casual%20wage%20work%2C%20the%20earnings%20disparity%20was%20higher%2C%20with%20women%20earning%20only%2060%25%20of%20what%20men%20earn.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUnfortunately%2C%20the%20share%20of%20women%20in%20self-employment%20has%20remained%20stagnant%20over%20most%20of%20the%20post-reform%20period%20(and%20has%20even%20increased%20during%20the%20Covid%20and%20post-Covid%20period).%20This%20is%20a%20matter%20of%20concern%20because%20the%20earnings%20gap%20is%20highest%20in%20the%20case%20of%20self-employment%2C%20with%20women%2C%20on%20average%2C%20earning%20only%2040%25%20of%20men%E2%80%99s%20earnings.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20984px)%2061vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2045vw%2C%20600px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F13190006%2FRatios.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22609%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F13190006%2FRatios.png%20609w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F13190006%2FRatios-300x138.png%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-692848%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22280%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ETable%3A%20CASI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHow%20do%20these%20disparities%20play%20out%20across%20the%20earnings%20distribution%3F%20As%20women%20move%20up%20the%20earnings%20ladder%2C%20are%20they%20earning%20closer%20to%20what%20men%20make%20or%20does%20the%20gap%20widen%20even%20further%3F%20Figure%201%20(below)%20gives%20us%20an%20answer%20to%20this%20question.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20each%20type%20of%20employment%2C%20we%20divide%20the%20earnings%20into%20ten%20groups%20representing%20the%20lowest%20(decile%201)%20and%20highest%20earners%20(decile%2010).%20As%20we%20see%20in%20Table%201%2C%20across%20the%20earnings%20distribution%2C%20self-employment%20has%20the%20highest%20gender-based%20earnings%20gap.%20By%20contrast%2C%20salaried%20employment%20has%20a%20much%20lower%20earnings%20gap%20and%2C%20in%20fact%2C%20this%20gap%20steadily%20narrows%20as%20one%20moves%20up%20the%20earnings%20distribution.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20top%20of%20the%20salaried%20earnings%20spectrum%2C%20women%20earn%2090%25%20of%20what%20men%20earn%2C%20on%20average.%20For%20self-employment%20on%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20the%20earnings%20gap%20is%20still%20high%2C%20with%20women%20earning%20around%2060%25%20of%20what%20men%20make.%20Although%20the%20gender%20earnings%20gap%20in%20self-employment%20narrows%20as%20one%20moves%20up%20the%20earnings%20distribution%2C%20it%20remains%20quite%20high.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20984px)%2061vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2045vw%2C%20600px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F13190515%2FRatios-by-decile.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22808%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F13190515%2FRatios-by-decile.png%20808w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F13190515%2FRatios-by-decile-300x214.png%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-692850%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22577%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EChart%3A%20CASI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ETrends%20in%20earnings%20gap%20over%20time%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOfficial%20estimates%20of%20earnings%20from%20self-employment%20have%20only%20been%20collected%20since%202017%2C%20whereas%20we%20have%20information%20on%20wage%20earnings%20from%20the%201980s%20onwards.%20Figure%202%20shows%20the%20long%20run%20trends%20in%20earnings%20gap%20for%20salaried%20workers%20within%20each%20quartile%20group%20over%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20984px)%2061vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2045vw%2C%20600px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F13190830%2FRatios-per-quartile-and-time.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22835%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F13190830%2FRatios-per-quartile-and-time.png%20835w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F13190830%2FRatios-per-quartile-and-time-300x210.png%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-692851%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22585%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EChart%3A%20CASI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EExplaining%20the%20trends%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EClearly%2C%20over%20time%2C%20there%20has%20been%20a%20narrowing%20of%20the%20earnings%20gap%2C%20particularly%20in%20the%20second%20and%20third%20quartiles.%20Two%20possibilities%20can%20explain%20this%20narrowing%20trend.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%2C%20gender-based%20discrimination%20in%20the%20labour%20market%20may%20have%20decreased%20over%20time%2C%20with%20employers%20treating%20men%20and%20women%20similarly.%20Or%20it%20could%20be%20that%20the%20very%20nature%20of%20women%20participating%20in%20the%20labour%20market%20(vis-a-vis%20men)%20has%20changed%2C%20with%20more%20educational%20attainment%20among%20women%20as%20well%20as%20an%20improvement%20in%20the%20kinds%20of%20occupations%20and%20industries%20they%20had%20access%20to%20within%20regular%20salaried%20employment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20mentioned%20earlier%2C%20over%20this%20period%2C%20a%20large%20change%20has%20occurred%20in%20the%20composition%20of%20the%20female%20workforce.%20Older%2C%20less%20educated%20women%20have%20exited%20while%20younger%2C%20more%20educated%20women%20have%20entered.%20Fewer%20women%20are%20employed%20in%20agriculture%20and%20more%20and%20more%20women%20are%20in%20the%20services%20sector.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fpandemic-exacerbated-identity-based-discrimination-india-labour-market%5C%22%3EHow%20the%20Pandemic%20Exacerbated%20Identity-Based%20Discrimination%20in%20India%E2%80%99s%20Labour%20Market%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20discern%20how%20much%20these%20compositional%20changes%20explain%20the%20changes%20in%20the%20earnings%20gap%20over%20time%2C%20we%20use%20a%20standard%20decomposition%20technique.%20The%20Kitagawa-Oaxaca-Blinder%20decomposition%20considers%20the%20average%20earnings%20difference%20between%20men%20and%20women%20and%20identifies%20the%20extent%20to%20which%20this%20difference%20can%20be%20attributed%20to%20%E2%80%9Cexplained%20differences%E2%80%9D%2C%20i.e.%2C%20differences%20in%20observable%20characteristics%20between%20the%20two%20groups%2C%20and%20to%20%E2%80%9Cunexplained%20differences%E2%80%9D%2C%20i.e.%2C%20differences%20in%20unobservable%20characteristics.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EObservable%20characteristics%20include%20education%2C%20marital%20status%2C%20number%20of%20children%2C%20industry%2C%20and%20occupation%20of%20employment.%20The%20unobservable%20component%20is%20often%20interpreted%20as%20measuring%20discrimination%2C%20but%20it%20can%20also%20include%20the%20effect%20of%20omitted%20characteristics%20for%20which%20data%20is%20not%20available.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETable%202%20shows%20the%20extent%20of%20the%20explained%20and%20unexplained%20components%20over%20time.%20From%201983%20onward%2C%20there%20is%20a%20steady%20decline%20in%20the%20explained%20component.%20This%20reflects%20how%20the%20characteristics%20of%20men%20and%20women%20in%20the%20labour%20market%20have%2C%20over%20time%2C%20become%20similar%20and%2C%20hence%2C%20explain%20less%20and%20less%20of%20the%20gender%20wage%20gap.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBy%202021-22%2C%20about%2080%25%20of%20the%20earnings%20gap%20is%20attributable%20to%20this%20unexplained%20component.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F13191854%2FOaxaca.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22876%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F13191854%2FOaxaca.png%20876w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F13191854%2FOaxaca-300x143.png%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-692853%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22417%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ETable%3A%20CASI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20increase%20is%20more%20dramatic%20in%20the%20case%20of%20the%20rural%20workforce%2C%20where%20more%20than%2090%25%20of%20the%20gender%20wage%20gap%20in%202021-22%20was%20not%20explained%20by%20workers%E2%80%99%20characteristics.%20But%20the%20period%20that%20saw%20a%20rapid%20rise%20in%20the%20female%20salaried%20workforce%20(1999%20to%202017)%20did%20also%20see%20a%20rise%20in%20the%20unexplained%20component%20in%20urban%20India%20as%20well.%20Thus%2C%20the%20finding%20is%20a%20general%20one.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFinally%2C%20the%20size%20of%20the%20gap%20itself%20increased%20substantially%20in%20rural%20India%20but%20the%20increase%20is%20much%20less%20pronounced%20in%20urban%20areas.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20larger%20conclusion%20is%20worth%20emphasising.%20The%20same%20period%20that%20saw%20a%20rapid%20rise%20in%20regular%20wage%20work%20among%20women%20also%20saw%20an%20increase%20in%20the%20unexplained%20part%20of%20the%20gender%20wage%20gap%2C%20usually%20attributed%20to%20discrimination.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20last%20two%20decades%20have%20seen%20a%20large%20churn%20in%20the%20Indian%20female%20workforce.%20The%20increase%20in%20the%20share%20of%20women%20as%20salaried%20workers%20is%20good%20news.%20However%2C%20this%20increase%20has%20not%20led%20to%20a%20systematic%20reduction%20in%20the%20unexplained%20earnings%20gap.%20Rather%2C%20educational%20convergence%20has%20revealed%20the%20potential%20role%20of%20discrimination%20in%20causing%20the%20gap.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEven%20with%20an%20increase%20in%20education%20and%20improved%20access%20to%20non-agricultural%20employment%2C%20women%20continue%20to%20earn%20less%20than%20men.%20But%20once%20again%2C%20it%20is%20encouraging%20that%2C%20as%20one%20moves%20up%20the%20earnings%20ladder%2C%20the%20gap%20reduces%2C%20which%20may%20reflect%20less%20discriminatory%20conditions%20for%20women%20in%20relatively%20more%20formal%20parts%20of%20the%20economy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETherefore%2C%20policy%20responses%20that%20encourage%20improved%20access%20to%20education%20for%20girls%20and%20enable%20the%20expansion%20of%20formal%20employment%20can%20help%20narrow%20the%20gap.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EAmit%20Basole%20and%20Rosa%20Abraham%20are%20faculty%20at%20Azim%20Premji%20University.%20The%20analysis%20presented%20here%20was%20assisted%20by%20Hami%20Ameen%2C%20Research%20Associate%20at%20Azim%20Premji%20University.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20article%20originally%20appeared%20in%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fcasi.sas.upenn.edu%2Fiit%5C%22%3EIndia%20in%20Transition%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%2C%20a%20publication%20of%20the%20University%20of%20Pennsylvania%E2%80%99s%20Center%20for%20the%20Advanced%20Study%20of%20India.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22pub